name: Lynda Johnston
text:
I appreciate this Just Love Coffee Cafe - Madison coming to my community! Long needed and I hope they do well!
Great service!  The club sandwich and grilled cheese sandwich have been well prepared and most tasty. The iced tea service was well stocked and without a bitter taste.
I highly recommend this business for any 'get away' moment or gathering.

name: Rachel Sullivan
text: SUCH A CUTE PLACE! Service was amazing, atmosphere is perfect, and the food & coffee were super tasty! The building was clean, tons of seating (inside and out!). Really great addition to Madison 👏

name: Indigo Bolt
text: Had the flying pig! Did not expect the bacon and sausage to be IN the waffle! Add the delicious sausage gravy and you have a meal that will stick with you through the day.

name: Joey Rogers
text: My food and desert were great.  It's really nice to have a new place like this in Madison.  I'll try the coffee next time.

name: Eveie Edgar
text: Came here to study with my mom and had a wonderful time! I got an iced matcha latte and my mom got a hot caramel macchiato. I like my matcha really sweet and this was perfect!

name: D F
text: Just an FYI. The employees do mot have masks on. Including those preparing your coffee and food. The food was ok. Cute place though.

name: Dustin Sutton
text: Great new place to eat with an all day menu that’s really diverse.  My girls and I had waffles and an omelette   The girls LOVED the waffles and I also enjoyed my omelette. Great latte, sausage, and bacon too. They have a good variety of gluten free options and a dedicated waffle iron for it plus changed their gloves while preparing it. I’m looking forward to a gluten free Nutella waffle in the near future when I can stand the calories.

name: Alan Bergmann
text: Three of us stopped for a late, late lunch.  We ordered the flying pig, berry berry bo berry, grilled cheese, cinnamon roll, and a chicken Cesar salad.  No the portions weren't small, we just went crazy for a minute while ordering.   Lots of seating and a little book nook inside.   The flying pig was really really good and came with a choice of sauces (I choose the maple syrup, the gravy, and the jalapeno mayo.)  The berry berry was nice with plenty of fruit. The grilled cheese was cheesy and the salad came with lots of chicken. Definitely a good place to eat. Definitely will go back.

name: Jeffrey Baker
text:
I've been working out of town so I just found it and invited my wife there for a Sat AM latte. We tried a couple of the signature drinks and they were great. Loved the atmosphere. Staff are all friendly and helpful. We'll definitely go back.
Food all sounded good but haven't tried it yet.

name: Sam Ortega
text: A nice place to just hang out. The breakfast burrito is pretty good but the specialty seems to be the waffles. Will have to try them next. My spouse loves coffee and enjoys their brews, I’m not one for coffee and wish they had more of a selection for non coffee drinkers. Cold teas, Kambucha, or fruit juices besides apple and orange juice.

resp.text: Thanks for the giving us a try and the kind words!  I apologize if a Barista did not walk you through all of our non-coffee offerings.  Did you know we can offer all of our loose leaf teas iced?  One of the local favorites is the Blueberry Rooibos with some vanilla syrup added.  We also make a limeade concentrate from scratch for our coconut limeade coolers, and offer fruit smoothies.  We look forward to seeing you again soon!

name: Melanie Bone
text: Great food, good coffee.  Outstanding service! Was slightly busy, but definitely worth the wait!

name: Junell Shue
text: Fantastic atmosphere, wonderful breakfast options and amazing coffee! The kiddos loved the books and games, and while it is busy on the weekends there was still enough room to sit and relax and really enjoy. There are sugar free options for the specialty coffee drinks, and gluten free food options made specifically on a gluten-free waffle iron. We will make this a regular weekend spot!

name: Kristen Dickerson
text: The staff was very friendly and helpful in answering my questions and providing recommendations when I asked for them. The food quality was amazing and a pleasant treat for me on a holiday weekend.

name: Stacey Harring
text: Everything was Great!!!  Service, food and cleanliness were all on point!  We will be back for sure

name: Steve Berry
text: Best cup of tea I have had in years. Excellent quality leaves served by a staff that clearly know what they're doing! Atmosphere is calm and refreshing. Looking forward to many more visits.

name: Michael Conniff
text: Nice place, staff was friendly and professional.

name: Rachel Davis
text: Every time I go there I feel so welcomed and the food & coffee there is amazing. Also a very chill place to relax, do some work, eat with friends, etc

name: Tara Vaughan
text: The food and coffee is delicious, and the service is quick. And even though it is often crowded you can always find a spot!

name: Kevin Stephenson
text: Awesome place with a great staff!

name: Claudia Sjullie
text: If you love Nutella the stuffed Nutella waffle is amazing. If savory is what you crave then the grilled Italian caprese is a must have! I’m in love with their lattes and cold brews too.

name: Thomas Hall
text: Coffee was okay.  BLT had a five star mayo blend, bread a bit dry, good bacon, wilted lettuce. I prefer Libby's, breakfast special, great value, taste and service.  Just Love has a wonderful location.

name: Audrey Brown
text: Found this cute little place about 5 min from where we live! Service is always perfect and the frappes are phenomenal! You can come here to study, work, or just to grab a quick bite to eat!

name: Randy Broussard
text: First visit to Just Love Coffee.  The Cafe Au Lait did not disappoint and the portion size was fantastic.  Will definitely go back!  I look forward to trying some of the food next time.

name: Melissa Ford
text: Wonderful place to meet friends or enjoy time with family.  The tables are always clean and the staff are friendly.  The food is unique, delicious and piping hot.  I hope everyone supports this great place so that it is around for a long time!

name: B
text: Very good coffee. Friendly staff.

name: Katelyn Hill
text: Very clean establishment with a fantastic atmosphere. I love the little book and board game section. The coffee was delicious, but the food what sort of bland and overpriced. To be fair, that's about what you expect in this sort of establishment so it wasn't a surprise. Well worth the visit to get a drink and relax

name: Joshlyne Villano
text: Found this place about a week ago and have been here at least 6-7 times now, which says a lot about my spending habits and how good it is. The coffee is great and the food is delicious! Very unique options for breakfast and lunch!

name: Laura Ellen Schoelles
text: This location of Just Love is an absolute pleasure. If you've enjoyed the owners' location in Huntsville, you now have a backup location in Madison. Our service was excellent, the food was very good, the atmosphere is light and bright and conducive to conversation and solo computer work kudos to the owners, this is a fantastic place.

name: David Johnson
text: Great staff. Good food and coffee.

name: Patty Gurley
text: Love their Caramel Frappe’! Delicious!

name: Robin Black
text: Cassie is the BEST!  She always remembers my drink and has a smile on her face. The entire staff is so attentive and friendly. Great place to eat, caffeinated, and work.

name: Veronique Couverchel
text: Great service, books and a little nook where one can read. Great coffee. Oh and I love their coconut limeade!

name: Doug Fitzpatrick
text: This really is a nice restaurant and coffee shop.  It is a big new facility but has the feel of an old small town coffee shop.  The workers are very friendly and go out of the way to make you feel welcome and help you out.  Also, the coffee is just incredibly good.  I highly recommend!!!

name: Alaythea Carroll
text: My daughter and I love to hang out here, great atmosphere. We’ve even played board games! Their hot tea comes in a great presentation and as someone with Celiacs I appreciate that they offer gluten free pre packaged desserts!

name: Layla Branae
text: I really love the family vibe of Just Love Coffee Cafe. Everyone is very nice and the coffee was so good. Highly recommend the cafe, especially the White Chocolate Tiramisu Latte.

name: Kuan Collins
text: Great local coffee shop!  Nice atmosphere and yummy coffee.  Who could ask for more?

name: Gary Carlson
text: My wife and I just love this cafe! The staff is terrific and helpful. We will be returning often.

name: S Fury
text: Just Love Coffee is a great place to get coffee and food. The staff is super friendly and professional. If you haven't tried it, you really need to go and try all their delicious coffees and tasty food.

name: Jp Creekmore
text: I tried it for the first time and will definitely be going back.  I got a waffle and a regular drip coffee - both were very good.  The environment was pleasant and the staff friendly.

name: paul cleveland
text: This is our second visit. Coffee is excellent. My wife and I enjoyed splitting the Berry Berry Bo Berry waffle and a Womlette. Both were very good and filling. We're looking forward to coming back!

name: Matt Powers
text: Coffee was delicious and comparable price to other chains. Their womlette and bacon tater were both incredible (and filling enough to split for lunch!)

name: Tina Martinson
text: Great atmosphere and co.fortable seating. Games and books available. Clean store.

name: Lucy Tucker
text: The coffee is wonderful and this is a great place to meet friends for a bite to eat.  They also have games, a reading area and a small table for children who want to color or read.  Bring your computer and get some work done too.  So thankful to have Just Love in Madison.

name: Keith Jackson
text:
Visited Spring 2021 (opening week)

Wonderful little coffee shop. This place has all the usual hot or cold coffee favorites with great sugar free options, plus a full food menu.. They cook everything in waffle makers, but that doesn't limit their selection.  All of their products (drinks and food) are fantastic.  They also have some amazing pastries at the front. The Rockslide Brownie is awesome.

There's plenty of wifi and seating room to relax, study, or work. Everything seemed clean and well organized. The staff is quick and friendly.  Will certainly go again.

name: Lauren Graf
text: An absolutely wonderful place! The menu selection is awesome and the vintage couches are super comfy. Fun games and books out on the tables. The lavender lemonade is the perfect balance of sweet and tart with the floral lavender notes. I’ll be coming back to this family coffee and tea bar next time I visit!

name: Deen Waddell
text: Our favorite place in Florence!!!! Delicious teas to be had here with interesting flavor combinations. Daughter loves the matcha lemonade with violet and lavender syrup 💜🍋💜🍋💜

name: Allen Blair
text: Great place! Good coffee and teas. I had a 12 oz Americano that was very good. They used the Bootlegger Blend (medium roast) from Prevail Coffee Roasters in Montgomery, AL. The Americano was $2.50. My wife and daughter tried the teas. They have lots of options on tea including some with lemonade mixed in. We enjoyed talking to one of the owners and will certainly try to visit again anytime we are in Florence.

name: Nicki Muhawi
text: You can tell that they love what they do here. And there is an appreciation for the art of coffee! Friend and I got a Chemex and an iced americano and both were great and made with care 😁

name: Chris Yang
text: Best coffee in town! Lavender and cayenne coffee is a must try.

Super cute aesthetic and friendly service. Gives me the small town vibes I moved here for. Lexie at the counter is so sweet! Definitely found my new spot in town ☺️

resp.text: Thanks for your kind words, BreAnna! Welcome to Morris!

text: I love this coffee shop. The atmosphere is so welcoming. I love the iced coffee and getting juice boxes for my kids. Then we share Nutella toast and its the perfect treat. The staff is great and so friendly.

resp.text: Thank you, Stephanie! We’re so glad to hear that your family has enjoyed visiting our shop!

text: Great coffee! Love the aesthetic and feel. The play place is fantastic!

name: Ariel Lloyd
text: This a such a wonderful and delightful place!! During Sunday Brunch they have a live sax musician who is just phenomenal (mix between older and current songs). Everything he played made me want to dance to the smooth jazz melody and even sing along sometimes 🤣. The ambiance is awesome with a rustic vibe and food was delicious. My Hubbie had a brunch/breakfast burger and I had the same except on a bean burger. Both were a “party in your mouth.” I don’t typically do reviews, but for my coffee shop and cafe lovers, this is a MUST visit!!! We stayed several hours working and reading during our Hurricane Ida evacuation. This is how we made lemonade out of lemons!!

name: Raya.
text: This has been my go to "office" lately. The wifi is amazing and the coffee is great. I usually will come and work on my laptop for several hours (they close at 3pm).

name: Reilly Wells
text: Favorite spot to study! The music and atmosphere are amazing, and the coffee was fantastic! Really neat seasonal drinks and great classics!

name: melvin rios
text: Entered near nine, it wasn't busy. Nothing but great experiences here. The bill was good for what you get. Similar to a cafe in Las Vegas I liked.

name: valerie allen
text: the beignets are delicious and so is the lavender blossom latte. the place reminds me of this one hotel i went to in nashville that was cool as hell and i could definitely see myself coming back, but on certain conditions. now you may be wondering why i’m giving 4 stars instead of 5 in an obvious 5 star venue, but my review lost an entire star because of the mediocre music choice. someone in the back is probably going through a rough time right now because i’ve heard a whopping selection of 4 taylor swift songs and 3 harry styles songs. whatever millennial cusper has their spotify connected to this god forsaken speaker, please reach out to a therapist, i’m concerned.

name: Aleta Hobbs
text: Sunday brunch here was great. Great live jazz and the service was fantastic! Shrimp and grits was my favorite although I also enjoyed a piece of the perfectly cooked chicken from my son's plate. I will return!

name: NikiAnn Johnson
text: This is an old fashioned cozy little place. Needed a quick stop but it would be a neat place to just go and sit. Latte was very good.

name: Yusuf Akemoğlu
text: I cannot praise this place enough. This is my first time in here and I instantly fell in love. Beautiful, comfortable space, extensive menu with great food options, and my latte was perfect. Ordering was simple and easy. Customer service was exceptional and welcoming. The girl behind the counter was super helpful. A total gem in Tuscaloosa.

name: Chris Riley
text: Nice atmosphere!

name: Jack Sweeney
text: What a wonderful addition to the Midtown neighborhoods! Soul Caffeine has a huge selection of hot and cold coffee drinks  as well as creative breakfast and lunch dishes. The place is very inviting...great place to grab a bite or to hang out with friends.

name: Robert Stephens
text: Great atmosphere and coffee. This location, in Mobile has a great menu. Definitely try one of the waffles. My only complaint is they need to learn what a Blonde is.My other local coffee shops have it.

name: jessi
text: Excellent cold brew! Nice space for meetings. They have... a LOT of choices. The menu is quite expansive and a tad intimidating if you don't know what you're looking for, but if you ask for a barista recommendation that helps! ☕ overall, nice place. Not too fancy but it's decent coffee that gets the job done.

name: Mark Ramey
text: Great coffee and food. A wonderful selection of options and helpful staff.

name: Chris Gilbert
text: Avocado toast was not very toasty. The spread was so cold that it dampened the texture of the toast. Cappuccino had a lot of milk. Would be great if dogs could come inside like other places in downtown.

resp.text:
Hey Chris, I’m sorry you didn’t have a great experience with us today. I was able to find your transaction and issue a refund. We want each visit to be awesome so thank you for your patience as our young team works on improving.

On the pet issue I wish we could be more accommodating but it’s again Alabama Health Code to allow non-service animals inside restaurants. The Alabama Legislature changed the rule this summer to allow pets in outdoor areas so your pet is welcome outside. Feel free to order using our app and say your inside and we’ll bring your order out. We love pets and hate being the bad guy but we’re required to follow the rule.

name: Daniel Thompson
text: Outstanding new addition to their Daphne location. Plus a full menu! Gorgeous interior.

name: kay valentine (prettykayreviews)

Now that I know where it is, I will be a regular.

name: Anne Bet
text: NEVER EVER GET GAS HERE. They upcharge the gas! What's the most important part of a gas station? The &#@!ing gas. I pulled in because the price was lower than all of the other stations. But only on the sign. I started pumping and things weren't adding up. I literally got out a calculator and my final price was 11 cents more per gallon than what the sign and the pump showed, which means the pumps are broken...or rigged. The cashier didn't know what to do so I had to walk away knowing that I over paid. I guess the BBB will sort this out.

I was additionally delighted to run into an old friend who I would not have seen if not for this "third space." If you live in Oneonta, AL or are just passing through, I suggest stopping by Rock Hill Coffee Co.!

name: Brad Donnelly
text:
Really smooth delicious one of a kind taste! Truly excellent roasting and custom techniques used to attain excellent coffee. Coffee beans come from Ethiopia and other Rain Forrest countries to give you the very best bean to be brewed into a little cup of heaven!

I know I have watched Sandy in their little roasting shop in Opelika and have seen first hand the roasting expertise that Sandy uses in customizing these wonderful coffee blends.

I love the Auburn City Blend it is wonderful!  If you have not tried Toomer's Coffees you are missing out on a real one of kind custom blended coffee!  Treat yourself to a couple of pounds of each of their blends you will never go back to another coffee brand.

resp.text: Go Brad! Thanks!

name: Pollyanna Brannan
text:
First time I had their coffee I knew it was different and in a GREAT WAY!! I met the owners and have to assume that their time spent living in South America is where they learned good coffee and why it's important to use direct trade coffee beans - truly ethically sourced coffee beans
I love that it is family owned and made in Alabama because I think it is important to buy local when you can and the product is quality. I even quizzes them to find out details that are important and found that they make sure it is low acid, infrared roasted!!!!!  That to me is great customer service putting the special effort into "doing it right!!!" Having fast inexpensive shipping is a bonus!!! <wink> but all of this makes me love the brand. Had to share!! How often does some one slow down to share a positive?! Not enough so I wanted to make sure I shared this one because they earned it!

resp.text: Thanks Pollyanna!

name: Viann Whitten
text: Toomer's Coffee Roasters is awesome! Mr. and Mrs. Toomer lived in South America so they know coffee. Many people have given up drinking coffee due to stomach sensitivity but you don't have to anymore! Toomer's Coffee Roasters uses an Infrared coffee roaster so no more bitter taste and no high acid, just smooth wonderful coffee. Toomer's Coffee Roasters has cheap fast shipping too. Love this company. Best kept secret in Auburn, Alabama.

resp.text: Thanks Vivian

name: Logan Moore
text: Toomers Coffee is phenomenal! The best coffee in Alabama let alone Auburn /Opelika area! Sandy and Trish have been around the world to hone their craft and have brought a world class roastery to Opelika! If you are in town for ballgames or shopping their new store front is very close to tiger town and totally worth the stop in! Best brewed coffee ever! Auburn City Blend, Snickerdoodle, Vermont Maple But...everything they do is great!

resp.text: Thank you! You're very kind.

name: JOE LEOS
text: I had the joy of speaking with the owner Toomer's Coffee about the different coffees and their tastes. I bought the following coffees Auburn City Blend, Colombian Supremo and Ethiopian Yigacheffe Aricha Gedio. The coffees were all wonderful in taste and aroma but our favorite is Auburn City Blend.  Please take time to drop by and pick up some of the best local coffees Toomer's Coffee has to offer.

resp.text: Thank you Joe for your affirming words! It's a pleasure to do what we do and serve those like you. Blessings.

text: I waited in line for at least 20 minutes. I ordered a caramel ribbon crunch. I got ice blended coffee. There’s no caramel, and there wasn’t any whipped cream. I asked if they were out. They had just assumed i didn’t want it. They put the whipped cream on for me, but failed to add the crunchy topping. It’s horrible and the service was not friendly.

text: The food is always warm and delicious but the service is horrible. I wait in line forever and I end up getting the wrong thing. Also, the same women is there every time I go and she is so rude! She rolls her eyes at me and doesn't greet me and never tells me my total, she just puts her hand out and waits for my card. PLUS their blueberry scones are very dry and not flavorful at all.

name: Noah Taylor
text: I was at UAB for the Science Olympiad event, and went in with a couple of friends. I wanted to try the Cherry Mocha Frappuchino and when I ordered, the lady working was somewhat rude and said, “No, I’m not making that because I’m here alone.” When there was only four of us in there and two people sitting and eating at a table. I went back later and got one when two people were working and she still acted annoyed about it.

name: James Drummond
text: The location is a franchise of sorts operated by Sodexo, the food service intermediary working on contract for the university. As a result, the service is not and will never be up to Starbucks's standards. This is less about the quality of the food & beverages, and more to do with the quality and friendliness of the servers. I personally have only had to deal with slow service, but that could happen at any time during a rush. The worst stories come from others; I have been around while the building was hosting an added-security event, which required the presence of LEOs; the baristas refused to provide him with a glass of water without charging him. At other foodservice locations in the same building and operated by the same company, not even students are charged for water glasses. That one event does a good job summarizing the apathy and disregard the employees have for their customers. Another critical issue is that this location doesn't accept Starbucks's own rewards program, which is extremely annoying after having signed up for the program just for the convenience of the location being in the same building that I work for. I've personally made a resolution to never purchase another item at this location again.

name: Matthew Pearson
text: Go to the one in Sterne. This place is a mess. Wrong size coffee, stale croissant, long wait.

name: Craig Winn
text: Open early and well staffed.

name: Tim Fisher
text: Good service, well-trained staff.

name: Hunter Jackson
text: They're stepping it up!

name: Nicholas Blackstock
text:
I'm not even a big sweets guy but I WILL be frequenting this don't shop for sure!

As mentioned, typically I'm not the one to crave ice cream, cake or donuts. I usually just don't. Even when purchasing donuts (or grabbing free ones for that matter) I always go for plain glaze. I've had other eclectic flavors and styles but they usually don't do anything for me. All that being said to say, I now crave sweets and it's because of these donuts!

Check my pics to see some of the variety that have. From fruity pebbles, to old fashion, to blueberry cake donuts they are all so tasty... It blows my mind. They can only get better with time too, which is scary but exciting. I'm sure there are flavors that are being fine tuned (the owner told me so) that weren't even out when I went. If and when you go, you MUST... MUST... MUST get the maple bacon donut! It's soooo good!

Coffee provided by O'Henry's is the perfect touch. I prefer the Jamaican Me Crazy blend, but there's a house blend as well. Oh, almost forgot... A couple of great breakfast sandwiches on deck as well (there were samples when I went). Both wrapped in baked donut dough!

Long Review Short... Visit this donut shop TODAY if only for the maple bacon! You won't regret it

resp.text: Thanks Nick! Come back soon!

name: Andrew Dorris
text: Amazing local donut shop!

resp.text: Thanks!

name: Keshia Murphy
text: Great local find! The donuts were fresh, light, and fluffy! We got a dozen with one of each kind available and each one was delectable. The staff was also quite caring and made sure our order was as we liked it. We will be back.

resp.text: Thanks LaKeshia! So glad you enjoyed your experience! Come back Soon!

However I quietly showed the lady with short hair. That there is a hair in my breakfast. Her reply was" well these things happen" no they do not just happen someone is not careful enough while baking and cooking. She replaced my breakfast however by that time I was done. it would have been a great place if they paid attention to their work and not rush to pack up for the day. We went around 9:40am

name: Hope Ryder
text:
My family has loved the Daylight Donuts on Valleydale for the last 7+ years. The service has always been great and we rarely, if ever, have any complaints. So we know what their typical level of service is. We were beyond psyched to see they were opening up a new location on Acton Rd, which is now closer to my mom's house. We have been to the Acton location many times over the past year and a half, thinking we'd have a similar experience to the Valleydale location. I'm so disappointed to say that EVERY single time I've gone, as well as all other family members, we've had a horrible experience! Overall, the customer service is terrible. The employees do not listen or don't pay attention to what you want or what you actually get. For example, this morning we went thru the drive thru. There was no one in line and no one in the store. We ordered 2 dozen glazed holes and 6 regular glazed. Easy enough, right?! We thought so.. But apparently not. We got the holes but when we got home and opened up the box, I couldn't believe it! Not one single regular glazed donut was in the box!! There was a chocolate covered, chocolate with sprinkles, a custard filled chocolate covered donut, sour cream, strawberry sour cream and blueberry cake donut! It seemed like we got someone else's order but no one else was there! When I tried to call the store, their answering machine picked up after several rings, so I left a message. After receiving such poor service, I can't even immediately speak to anyone about it!! It is impossible to understand how these 2 locations share the same name. That's the only thing they have in common. I
We've also been incorrectly and outrageously charged during another trip. They charged us over $30 when the correct total was no more than $15. This wasn't the first time we've been given the wrong items. My sister and mom went during a slow time. No other customers were there in the drive thru or inside. They ordered a dozen assorted donuts and 2 large coffees. The girl ended up handed them 2 big boxes of donuts and a large and medium coffee. Then proceeded to charge them a price that was way more than what they had ordered. My sister told the girl they hadn't received the right order and gave the boxes back. After a while of waiting, they were given another box of donuts. However, they were still being charged the same price as before for the 2 dozen donuts, even though they'd given 1 box back, that they never even ordered to begin with. My sister had to explain to her that they'd given the second dozen back and that they only ordered one dozen. Eventually she corrected the total. But after all that, they didn't even bother addressing the wrong coffee size they received. When they got home, of course the order wasn't right. They had 2 chances to correct the order and still failed. That's ridiculous! We have not had a single good trip to this location. Most visits have been during extremely slow times when no other customers were at Daylight. It doesn't make sense how it's consistently so awful when they're only taking care of 1 customer.
In addition, the donuts we have had there do not taste nearly as good as what we've had at the other location. That is not just my opinion. Several other family members have said the same.
We've given this location more than enough attempts to get better so we do not intend to return, except to get our money back for our wrong order today. We'll stick to the Valleydale Daylight and I recommend the same to others!

resp.text: Hope, we are so sorry for the experiences you have had at our Acton Rd location. What you have described is definitely not what we are wanting our customers to experience when you visit us. If you would please contact me via email at magiccitychris@gmail.com, we would love to get some more information from you to try to make this right. I hope to hear from you soon. Again, very sorry for the experience you had today.

name: Brian Morgan
text:
Nestled in DeKalb County is this great, small little coffee shop. The town of Geraldine is slow, and often only acts as a destination that people pass through on their daily routine. Frothy Dog, though, makes it so that the town of Geraldine is worth stopping IN for a visit.

Northeast Alabama, as a region, is hungry for proper specialty coffee, and only Frothy Dog has stepped up to the plate to truly satiate that hunger. It does a lot of things rights. Their blended drinks are popular, their Chicken Salad Sandwich is a cut above, but their espresso based coffee? That's the magic of the shop. That's where this shop excels. It takes great care in tuning, and extracting the best cup of coffee, and the owners are very knowledgeable about the craft and art of coffee. There's no other coffee shop like it in the area.

If you're a resident in DeKalb County, or in Geraldine itself, and haven't tried Frothy Dog out yet, do yourself a favor, and make that trip. The owners do a great job of walking newcomers to coffee through their first cup. Sometimes it's a full jump for those who are ready to enjoy the world of espresso, and sometimes you're eased in with a sweet, blended beverage. No matter what, you will not disappointed with your drink.

Anyone new to coffee will love their dark Mocha, and the Coconut Dark Mocha are also great drinks. I love both as an avid coffee drinker as well. I recommended for the regular coffee drinker, their 12oz regular latte with an extra shot of espresso, or just a two shots of espresso by itself and a cup of ice water if you're feeling adventurous. Amazing espresso, quality shop.

text: A+ on the hot caramel macchiato. I had it once and went back for another. Perfect temp and the mix is exactly how the macchiato should be. I tried the lunch: SouthWest Panini and chips. Came with an apple slice and Cheetos. Great sandwich! I would have preferred a pickle instead of the apple. The hot sandwich gave the apple a bit of a taste.  I would have preferred a choice of chips but all in all good little lunch. Maybe there is a way to choose but I didn’t see it on the QuickCup app. Green tea frappe was nice. Very refreshing. The cup is a little flimsy and definitely easy to pop the top or drop with a heavier frappe. Especially handing it out the drive thru. I think the QuickCup service could be better. I ordered early but had to wait on my sandwich to be made after arriving but the sandwich definitely was worth the wait. My drinks were ready when I arrived.  I’m glad Geraldine has a little spot for the coffee lovers in town. I definitely think the employees are friendly and the place wil be very popular for the younger crowd in town.

Again, not warmed up enough. I tried to order the same drink I LITERALLY ordered on Friday and she lied about them not making it anymore. I mentioned that I had just ordered it on Friday. She got snippy and made it but it wasn't correct. I told her(which took a lot for me) that it wasn't supposed to be warm. She rudely said "you didn't say ice. I never have said iced and have always gotten it the way I like it. Then she makes another one and I tell her how it's supposed to be BUT NOPE! Still wrong. text: The food here was amazing and the staff was very friendly and even gave us some fresh orange juice to sample.  The wait for our to-go order was on the long side and the prices were higher than most places nearby (about $8 for a sandwich), but the quality of the food was outstanding and it was well worth the wait and the price.  All of the produce is clearly very fresh and the portions were generous.  The sandwiches come with amazing seasoned chips (or crackers?  I'm not sure what they are other than delicious) and salsa as well as a few pieces of fresh fruit.  I can't wait for my next opportunity to go back.

name: Quinn Calvert
text:
A small place with a quaint sort of homely feel. I got the Sicily sandwich, and it was phenomenal - exactly the sort of Italian flavors I was looking for on a hot summer day. The sides are fairly limited, but the chips and salsa aren't bad. Couldn't help but feel the salsa was lacking something: a zest, tang, spice, idk. It just seemed a bit too bland.

But that's really the only demerit. Overall a great mix of value, flavor, and portion size.

name: Stephanie Pierce
text: I went to Sady's Bistro today, 4/18/15, with my mom and the experience wasn't great. I believe it opens at 8 and we got there around 8:45. When we walked in there was one lady ahead of us and she was told by the workers in the back that the server had not arrived yet. We had been waiting a few minutes when finally the server showed up. My mom ordered spinach and egg crepes and I ordered what I thought was a quesadilla with basil goat cheese. We sat down and my mom's crepes came out fairly quickly and I continued to wait. After maybe 10 minutes the server came back and said that they were out of basil goat cheese so I switched fr another and waited. While I was still waiting a couple that had ordered after us both got their meals and mine had yet to come. Finally after maybe 25 minutes mine finally arrived. it was 2 tiny toasted tortillas a few slices of tomato and a little cup of goat cheese and 2 pieces of bacon. When we asked why it had taken so long she basically just blamed the workers in the back and gave a rushed sorry as she walked away. I just found the whole experience very off-putting and do not think I will be returning.

name: Dustin Ingram
text: Easy to miss from 1st Ave as it is tucked in a short strip, but do not be deceived! Piper and Leaf has a wide and flavorful selection of hot and iced teas, samples available, and answers for all your questions. They also have a beautiful gift sample set. The Briar Patch tea is so tasty. This will be a regular stop on every future visit to Birmingham, but I may also take to their website to supplement in the meantime.

name: Carrie Rollwagen
text:
The magic of Piper & Leaf starts with the tea itself — it's phenomenal. They use a lot of locally sourced ingredients, and the flavors are unbelievable. The Old Fashioned Birthday Cake really does taste like birthday cake (I even get the unsweet version, and it still tastes that way — I don't understand it, but I'll take it.) I also love their chais and their seasonal flavors — well, it's really all pretty great.

Piper & Leaf is famous for their jars of iced sweet tea and their flavor selection, but they can also do unsweet tea and any of their teas hot as well. They have teas available to order and drink, and they also have loose leaf and sachets available. (Their loose leaf teas come in bags that can also act as tea strainers in a pinch, which is pretty great.) The loose leaf teas come with instructions for how to brew a cup of hot tea, a jar of iced tea, or even as a bigger batch if you're brewing for a large group. This location has coffee as well.

I've always had the friendliest service at Piper & Leaf — they take time to hear you out, help you find the tea that will work best for you, and make sure you leave happy. I couldn't recommend them more; their fans are extremely dedicated, and for good reason.

name: Grace
text:
Piper and leaf has definitely set itself apart from all other tea joints. The first time I tried P&L was in Huntsville and I was extremely excited when I heard about the Birmingham location. We can all take pride in this locally owned business and their down to earth attitude! My first time visit to the Woodlawn location was very similar to Huntsville, great people willing to serve and fill you in on anything you would like to know about the tea! Sammy is a wonderful employee and very helpful.

I love that they keep their customers up to date via social media at all times.
It's always worth the trip and I look forward to their possible grand opening in August.

name: Zana Griffin
text:
I would love to speak to whomever is the owner of this new establishment to inform them of an incident I witnessed in their business regarding the way the staff poorly handled a situation involving a potentially homeless man.

Coffee taste great though.

In response to your reply:

Firstly, I'm truly sorry about what happened to your wife. I do hope she is doing ok from the interaction with the man.

And I am sorry to put it so plainly, and I don't mean to be unkind, but how are you even sure that you know who I am and what exactly is the issue I needed to address?

How are you sure that you were in the building at the same time I was - because a man who comes in 2 or 3 times a day happen to be there?

I don't believe our interactions are the same because you just informed me you wouldn't give him any coffee, but when I walked in he did have coffee, which led to the series of events that brought me here.

However, if you were there at the same time I was, as you assume, then you already know my complaint because you witnessed it happen, and perhaps do not believe it is warranted, and that really is all I need to know.

(When responding to the next Guest's concerns, please let them tell you what it is before assuming you know what the problem may be and volunteering a response -- once again, I truly am not trying to be rude - which is what delayed this response to find the kindest way to put it, because I have no desire in arguing with someone over the internet. I only reached out this way because it seemed the most professional and I work in the same industry and thought you as a owner of a new business would want to know. Just a kind suggest from someone who was very excited to have a local coffee shop, only to be let down on the first try.)

resp.text:
Update: Oh, so stop by anytime to let us know what you saw and are talking about because your comment popped up just minutes after he was violent so I assumed you were speaking about what I described below, sorry about that.

Glad you like our coffee.  What you missed about the incident was that the man started getting angry, yelling, and lunged at my wife in a violent manner.  My wife was simply talking to him.  I ran there to stop him from becoming more violent and I was about to call the police but he calmed down after I spoke strongly to him.  After he calmed down he asked us for free coffee, we always give him free coffee when he stops by (sometimes he stops by two or three times a day).  I said no coffee because he was angry and mean and told him to leave.  I'm sorry you didn't like the way I handled the situation but I was concerned he was going to get violent but I’m sure glad he didn’t.

It would make you feel at home, on a cold winter morning. There muffins and bagels are also really good. The only reason i didn't give 5 stars is because the prices are a little bit high. Other than this, it is a really good spot to get a cup of joe before you go to work.

name: G M
text:
We moved here via Seattle and Southern Oregon.  Coffee is in our blood!! We were delighted when Pine brothers opened in Rainsville! Most of all, we love that Heather is manager there. She is outstanding. She knows her regulars, their coffee and even their music preferences. When I was there, a mom came up to the counter to buy an apple for her little daughter. Heather made sure that the apple was fresh and firm, moreover, she washed and dried the apple before giving to the kid.  Extraordinary!!!
Dr. G.

Won't get my money again. The one in the Auburn Kroger is great. This is the only one that I've encountered employees who were so rude. The drinks were good though.

text: We just ordered cappuccinos and I’m not sure they knew how to make them or maybe just didn’t care. There was a single espresso shot and then she spooned in the top of the frothed milk - no blend of the two. No heated milk at all - that was poured down the drain.  This was repeated twice as we ordered two - I’d guess at least 3/4 pint of milk was poured down the drain. I’ve never seen anything so bad from Starbucks. When I said I’m not sure these were made correctly she says they were. I left them instead of getting a replacement bc they didn’t  know how to make them the first time and my husband waited 15 mins for them.

name: Trupti Shinde
text:

Cafe is very clean and comfortable seating.

Definitely recommend

name: Opal Hall
text: Having the grilled cheese! They have soup and some other options. For winter they have different latte and hot cocoa options. Beautiful colors and location. Lots of treats and cute little gifts. They’re having a birthday party here at the moment. It was kind of out of our way, so I will probably go to the original location, but it seems like a nice spot.

name: Beth C
text: Very friendly and knowledgeable staff. They can have gluten free cupcakes available with a little notice! The macarons are beautiful, and they have ice cream and sorbet. You need to stop by!

resp.text: Thank you Beth!

name: Erin Shockey
text:
I wish i could give Dreamcakes Cafe a million star review! Wow! I visited Dreamcakes Cafe with my mother and sister for afternoon tea. It was such a special day for us because we planned afternoon tea right before they accompanied me to shop for my wedding dress! The staff knew this and were so excited, kind, and encouraging.

We made our tea selections a few days before our event via email. Kallie was wonderful about responding on email. We had to sign a contract prior to the tea and she made it very easy to do so. When we arrived to the cafe, our tea table was set up with everything we needed: teacups, utensils, saucers, even fresh flowers! The set up was stunning and the food was delicious! I highly recommend the pimento cheese sandwich with peach jam and the macarons!!

During the tea, the wait staff made us feel so special. Someone was always by to ensure we had everything we needed, refill cups, etc and all of them were SO polite, friendly, and knowledgable about tea selections. My sister had a gluten and dairy allergy and they made sure she knew what she could and couldn't eat and even brought out a special cup of chicken salad for her.

Thank you Dreamcakes staff! You made this such a special day for us. The thought and time you put into the details of our tea was noticed and SO appreciated. It was perfect from start to finish. Hope to see yall again soon... we will be back!!

resp.text:
Thank you so much Erin! It was such a pleasure working with you. We really enjoyed serving you during your tea and are so happy that you enjoyed it so much! We are pleased to accommodate all allergies and love that we were able to find the best solution for your sister. We love going above and beyond for you customers! We look forward to seeing you in the future!

- Dreamcakes Cafe Staff

name: Kathy McLaurin
text: Good cupcakes! Was a little upset that I asked for a wedding cake cupcake and after arriving home, realized they gave me a vanilla cupcake instead. I’m not a fan of plain vanilla anyway, but I didn’t finish it- the frosting had a slight “soap” taste to it. For $5 a cupcake I’m not sure it was worth it. However, I loved the other flavors provided! My advice: don’t get the vanilla, and make sure you check to make sure you pay for the cupcakes you actually want! I would have gone back, but they were already closed and it’s a 15 minute drive from where I live.

text: Had an apple cider, brownie and muffin. None of them was too sweet, which is a great plus for me. Great quality of the ingredients, tasted like it is homemade. They deserve a 4.5 grade

Hi Mr Alharethi,

The bathrooms are and have always been horrendous. However it is the best stocked store I have visitited and the pizza is imoressively good....when its cooked all the way. 9/10 youre just eating cheese and raw dough. I miss how great this place used to be. Save for the bathroom. A few small changes would go a long way.

name: Robert Hughes
text:
Consistently the worst experience.  Want a sandwich with tomatoes?  They're out of tomatoes.  Want a sandwich with cucumbers? Out of cucumbers.  What about a bagel sandwich with bacon?  Out of bagels and bacon.  How about customer service?  All out of that too. But there's plenty of awful selection and rude attitude directed at their customers.

I ordered a bagel sandwich with bacon, the were out of bagels, and got no bacon.  I went back to ask about my missing bacon and was rudely told "We don't have no bacon", then the employee stormed off.  I will forego lunch and drive off campus from now on; no more 3-4x weekly visits to this awful place.

I've never asked for anything on my bagel to be changed to suit my taste/dietary requirements but it's never been a problem when I've seen other people ask.

text: I dont know if it is because it is on a college campus, but the prices are higher than other einsteins I have been to. The food is good and the staff is friendly. Can get busy during lunch

text: Quant place with good selection to choose from. Staff very friendly and eager to help. Good prices and pleasant atmosphere.

text: Always have good coffee.

name: Chucri Jalkh

name: Shaun Osborne
text: The prices are well in line with the likes of Starbucks, etc. The location is excellent and we enjoyed the visit. To be fair, it wasn't a busy time when we went and the people were extremely nice. I had my mother and wife with me and was very interested in getting nice people, even if they couldn't make coffee. All in all, we had a great time and the coffees were great. They were very inviting and homey.

name: Thomas Garner
text: Amazing cappuccino with foam, My friend loves the iced chai tea. Plenty of food options as well. If you visit go upstairs because there are several rooms even one with windows with a view of downtown and the courthouse. If you're lucky you can use the bluetooth speaker and play your own tunes(just don't get caught lol).

name: Kaleb Thurman
text: Our weekly home away from home.  Very enjoyable beverages and menu items.  Inviting atmosphere.  Sit long enough and sip enough beverages and you never know who you will run into.  Wonderful place to just enjoy the company of others.

name: Sarah Jordan
text: One of my favorite coffee bistros in Huntsville.  Local flavor, local art and unique decor. I love the friendliness of the staff.  Highly recommended! Make sure you check out the rooms upstairs. Tons of seating.

name: Anna Parker
text: I've gone in this place 3 different times and 3 different times I've left without anything. The service is awful.  I've gone in waited 10 min without seeing anyone there working to take a. Order. Went in tonight and 2 workers were in the back prepping food while me and another customer waited 5 minutes for someone to take her order.  I eventually left because of how slow they were to even acknowledge us. I don't know how this place stays open. I'm hoping a decent coffee shop will open at the downtown square because Huntsville can use one

resp.text:
Anna,

This is from Cathy. one of the owners of A Cup Of Everything.

Thank you so much for letting us know about this. I will be discussing this with our managers. We work hard to offer great customer service and apologize for for your experience..

Cathy

name: Max Parks
text: Didn't try the coffee, but the pastries were top notch, as was the service. You can go into the cosy rooms upstairs and stay for hours; I went to find a quiet place to do some writing, and felt welcome every time. Absolutely delightful. 5/5

name: Justin Bzdell
text: I go to A Cup of Everything at least once a week. I just love there freshly brewed coffee. The WiFi is  excellent for studying on some school work. I highly suggest the coffee!

name: Zachary Garcia (zakzackzachary)
text: Only store open downtown on 4th of July and the staff was super friendly. 3* from me because the smoothie which was essentially syrup and blended ice was like a cup of tasteless foam and was almost $6. Maybe their other stuff is better though, I can't speak to it.

resp.text: Zachary, we hate to hear that your smoothie wasn't good. Can we make you another to hopefully redeem ourselves?

name: Sally Wise
text: We come here regularly - terrific crafted coffee and tea beverages, plus local craft beer! Great snacks, locally made gifts, and more. Friendly service. Check out the art gallery upstairs, and there is free wi fi

name: Jacque Brandon
text: Not sure which owner the previous ratee met I found both owners to be friendly and gracious.   The food was excellent and the coffee some of the best I've ever had. A cute little bistro enviroment relaxing and very welcoming.

name: Lucas
text: Expensive coffee with mediocre service. I paid almost five bucks for a small  black coffee and a shot of espresso. I've been there a few times, only really if I have to use the bathroom downtown early in the day. Never heard them once say "welcome to cup of everything", or "thanks for stopping by sir!". Just seems like the staff is generally upset to be there.

resp.text:
Mr. LukiPooki

I am one of the owners of A Cup of Everything. I am very sorry you hear that you have has such poor service at ACoE. Please know that we appreciate yours and all our customer's business. If you like I eill be happy to meet you at the shop and I will personally refund you your money.

Regards
Cathy Lamberth
Clamberth@acupofeverything.com

name: Nicholas Thompson
text: It seems as though as this establishment cares more for speedy service rather than quality. The atmosphere is lackluster and the employees seem very disinterested in providing a quality experience that one would expect of a privately owned coffee shop.

name: Stormii L
text: Nice. Love to go sit upstairs on my lunch break.

name: Katheryn Young
text:
A Cup of Everything Convenience Store is truly convenient--a menu loaded with coffees, teas, and sandwiches primarily; and a medium-sized cache of snack bars, bottled and canned drinks, chips, and even things like headache medicine, this little restaurant/shop is a wonderful addition to the Square in downtown HSV. In addition to having just about anything you might find yourself needing while out on a stroll around downtown, or serving jury duty, etc., the staff is incredibly friendly and will (in my experience) go out of their way to ensure your good day.
However, you will be paying convenience store prices for most of their selections: a cup of coffee will only leave you a little better off than a visit to Starbucks (without the carefully constructed flavor--ACoE's coffee has been particularly bitter in my experience, even with sugar and cream), and the food can get a little pricey as well. Packaged foods, on the other hand, seem to be a bit cheaper than, say, the store inside the courthouse but it's not really enough to keep me from driving the little extra distance to the Publix at Twickenham Square.
The cozy atmosphere and neat meeting space upstairs, though, may be enough to counter-balance the slightly higher prices and not-so-awesome coffee--and a warm Spring day sat outside with a cold cup of iced tea and a fresh-made sandwich can't quite be beat.
So all-in-all, if you don't mind spending a bit more and not getting Starbucks-quality coffee, you will get a cozy, unique atmosphere great for a refreshing time on your own or with friends.

name: Super Frivolous
text:
Was soooo good.  Had a rough Friday and came in and asked for a Chocopresso, one shot expresso, one shot chocolate wine, topped with whipped cream and chocolate sauce. Took the edge right off and had served by the sweetest batista.

Would def get again.

resp.text: Thank you so much. Glad you enjoyed the drink. It is yummy.

name: Stephen Beier
text: Great tasting coffee, little over priced. Owner was rude during my visit.

name: Elijah Boyd
text: Quiet little shop with food and convenience items. If you need something when you're downtown try here.

name: davelant
text: A convenient place downtown for a sandwich and a cup of coffee.  (Good Kaffeklatsch-roasted cofee)   Pre-made Happy Tummy sandwiches usually available, as well as sandwiches made to order with chips, yoghurt, fruit and fruit cups for sides.  Good wifi and a lot of room upstairs, including a view over the courthouse square.  Both of the owners have been gracious to me.

name: Adam Evans
text: Terrible attempt at a cappuccino, bright, loud atmosphere, minimal seating.  If all you need is caffeine, it'll do.  For anything else, go elsewhere.

name: Usman Zafar
text: Good coffee , nice place

resp.text: Thanks Usman. Appreciate your visit.

name: Savannah Beier
text: Bad customer service, owner was extremely rude. I will not be going back.

name: Sandy Toomer
text: Great coffee of course, but owner has his own stuffed grape leaves, hummus, and other unique homemade food items. Great atmosphere too! Unlike St******s, coffee is not bitter and they have decent seating and want you to stay

name: Samantha Chace
text: My boyfriend and I discovered this place this weekend and it's our new favorite spot! The owner is so friendly and remembered us instantly when we came back a second time. My boyfriend loves the Turkish coffee. We are graduate students and it's a quiet and friendly atmosphere to come get some writing or studying done. We will definitely be back!

name: Kent Scruggs
text: World Cup is a nice little coffee shop.  Nothing really makes it that special, but they have good coffee for reasonable prices.  It's definitely better than the Starbucks across the street, that's for sure.  It's typically quiet and not very busy, so it's a good place to go chat with your friends and drink good coffee.  They don't try to be pretentious or anything like other coffee shops in town, which is cool.

name: Lucas Elmore
text: The coffee shop for people getting things done and for introverts. Usually very quiet. Their Brazil French press is the best coffee I’ve had in Auburn, and the place is very clean and isn’t crowded like the downtown coffee shops 99% of the time. Kind of a European vibe. Highly recommend. Probably my favorite coffee shop in Auburn.

name: Victoria Lynn
text: Very quiet interior back room which is appreciated by the nearby med students and nursing students! The staff is also so friendly, and their food is unusual for a coffee house (lots of Mediterranean options!) but absolutely delicious. I like how the shop is divided into a louder, more social front room and a quieter back room area.

name: Parker Wilson
text: Can confirm claims of best Chai in Auburn. In terms of flavor, imagine a cherub descending from heaven to gently pour vanilla chai directly into your soul, filling you with peace and serenity unbeknownst to this world. My buddy got a Turkish coffee and the presentation made me feel like I was heir to a eastern european dynasty.

name: Rachel Witt
text: I was in Auburn for work a couple days ago and asked for a recommendation for the best coffee. I’m so glad I was directed to WCCC! I ordered a Turkish coffee, which I haven’t had since I was in Morocco, and it was excellent! The owner is really friendly, he loves his customers, and he’s great for a conversation! He also knows his middle eastern food. I made a point to go back that day for lunch, and I ordered a hummus with pita bread and chips—more authentic deliciousness! The atmosphere is just what you want in a cafe, and the decor is beautiful and fascinating. I’m coming here every time I’m in Auburn! Don’t let this gem get run out by Starbucks!

name: J Patel
text: I have been coming here for many months and have loved the service. You get what you pay for also in a great price. I came saturday (1/28) and was very disappointed with the service and quality of the food that i received. I will never be purchasing anything from the employee who was working even though she was very sweet she was not able to handle the load of the customers to provide what was ordered. The experience here definitely matters with who is working. The owner is great also.

name: Joey May
text: Has new owner who really cares for his customers. Has great coffee and treats to offer with reasonable prices. Nice quiet and quaint place with pleasant atomsphere. So grab your kindle or tablet and a cup of coffee with a treat and enjoy!

name: Fitnikks 2.0
text: Love this place! Great place to study great, food and drinks and the workers are always so nice! The owner also workes behind the cash register almost every time I come, making the coffee shop as a whole feel more personable. Its really nice to feel truly welcomed to a coffee shop.

name: Conor Croft
text: Lots of different coffee and tea choices which are all very good. World Cup Coffee has a fairly quiet atmosphere good for doing work and studying, the 5G internet is pretty good. There are some larger tables in the back if you need to work with a group. There are also many food options and patio seating out front.

text: Love the hot chocolate.  Excellent service and great place to meet with friends.

name: Jake Horigan

Very pleasant workers and great experience overall. Oh, and my girlfriend and I are always pleased with the specialty lattes!

name: James Joyce
text: The real deal. The location is great for me, and the selection is good. Get anything from flavored iced to Turkish coffees. Prices are a little higher than Dunkin, but not absurd for a local shop.

name: Lauren Mazzola
text: Try the Southern Pecan coffee it is the best! World Cup Coffee is a perfect place to relax and enjoy a nice cup of coffee. Would highly recommended!

text: Great atmosphere; great service; friendly staff.

name: AARON MCGREW

Sandy and Trish are the friendliest people that I have every encountered who own a coffee shop.  I work from home so frequent the place 2-3 times a week.  The coffee is out standing and roasted right here in AU!  The Oatmeal Steamer is my favorite food that they serve and is from Trish's Missionary days.

Check it out!

I always felt like I was being shaken down before they would hand over the caffeine.. so I just stopped going. Glad I can finally stop for coffee here before work again. It’s quick and conveniently located and everything (coffee and bagel sandwiches) have been good!

text: Coffee and breakfast sandwiches/muffins are okay. The customer service is kind of lacking and a bit overpriced since one coffee and a sandwich is more expensive than Starbucks.

name: Aaron the Nomad
text: Blank is simply a cozy coffee shop that has great vibes. It is the perfect place to get a Quick coffee or just sit and do some reading. The environment is calm, peaceful, and always has some classic tunes playing.

name: Spencer Williams
text: Loved it! I was visiting from out of town and needed a place to chill. The two staff I met were super friendly and cool, they let us play board games while we hung out. Food options are limited to muffins, but they have a decent drink selection. Small comic and record selection, but a really awesome place.

resp.text: Out of towners are our favorites. You guys get it! We get you, too.

name: Andrea Lindholm
text: Keishun is wonderful and makes an excellent cup of coffee! Love it.

name: Jay B
text: Interesting collection of things being sold in the shop. Nice little place. I think a weekly group was there playing d&d at the only table in the shop. We ordered our drinks and left.

name: Chris West
text: I love the shop. Totally cool retro look. Love the patio area out back. The guys that run the store are great to talk to and know what they are talking about when it comes to comics and anything else they sell. They are super nice guys.

name: Timothy Green
text:
Came in for a coffee. Server who was going to prepare my drink wiped his nose audibly across his open palm while waiting at the register for my order. Gross. Hard pass.

Update: Check out the Owner's response to this review. Just lovely. I never ordered btw, just excused myself politely and left. Find coffee elsewhere mates! Ye be warned.

resp.text: I prefer to give people an OPPORTUNITY to wash their hands before PREPARING my beverage. Otherwise my daily triggering isn't as fair as the safe place Im constantly demanding.  Those computer screens, along with cash and cards are much grosser that you'd think. Washing hands before TAKING the order just creates the need to wash them again. We wash hands 100% of the time before making ANY beverages. ALWAYS HAVE AND ALWAYS WILL. But yeah, that's gross, and probably embarrassing to the guy attempting to take your order. Downright deplorable. You know that feeling right?  We've all been there and it ALWAYS happens at the worst possible time.  What matters though, really, is the recovery. I hate that you had to leave so abruptly though, as you missed the part where he washed his hands before preparing the drink you ordered. It was good too. I know because I drank it. We love you either way. Even when we don't meet your expectations. We will put your feedback to good use and make it a learning experience.  It is our mission to look to the past and improve the future!!

name: Scot McKinney
text: Super customer service, great coffee, awesome selection of records and comics. A great place to shop and hangout, plus the patio is sweet!

name: N Flippo
text: If the city of Florence was a store, this would be it... Great coffee and drinks (try the coffee milkshake), a varied collection of comics as well they are willing to order for you if they don't have something, and vinyl records from vintage to new. Definitely stop by to grab a drink and browse or sit on the back patio!

resp.text: Word is bond

name: Will Mitchell (Captain Will)
text: I may visit others, but this is MY comic shop.  It's a small place because they've just got started, but the folks are great, and so is the coffee.  There's lots of vinyl records, if you're into that sort of thing.  My wife and I stop in at least once a week, and they're making comic collectors out of the both of us!

name: Tiffany Kilburn
text: Absolutely amazing caramel macchiato, (not overly sweet like Starbucks) Patrick was very friendly and informative. Lovely Patio to just chill while enjoying your coffee. Will definitely be a added delight to my normal routine.

resp.text: We appreciate your kind words Tiffany!

text: Delicious doesn't begin to describe the food. We ordered lunch and dinner to-go as we were passing through the town. The Kale wrap and Jack fruit BBQ sandwich are our top picks. A great mission accompanied by delicious food and awesome service. I will be back soon even if I have to drive out of the way.... I may even plan a trip just to eat here again!

name: Duzle
text: The café itself is quaint and chill, and the lady who runs it is charming and lively! Street parking. The location is within their home community, to which they wish to give back by providing a healthy alternative such as this. I had the "millionaire 'burger'" along with sweet potato fries - quite tasty! It was piled high with veggies, avocado, and other add-ons. The burger look and texture was great. As usual with meat substitutes, you must treat it as a new kind of "meat" rather than compare it to actual beef. If you do this and let it stand on its own, this burger (along with other substitutes) tastes great. Next time I'm here, I want to try the jackfruit "pulled pork" and possibly a smoothie. This was my first vegan restaurant experience and it was quite lovely! Highly recommended for those hesitant on exploring this new type of cuisine.

text: I've been here twice and each time was a pleasant experience. If you are in a rush, call in your order. The Happy Feelings Tropical Good Smoothie is the best. I've also tried the pulled pork sandwich which was surprisingly good if you're not vegan. Check them out for good healthy food.

name: cottonwood rescue
text:
Dunkin' let me tell y’all about the team at 1865 E. Main St. Dothan😍 This team is always the most friendly and helpful I have ever experienced at Dunkin’💯 & I have visited them from Panama City Beach to Tallahassee, to Birmingham to Gainesville & no other compares to my home store!🤞🏼As an Emt I’m on the go with 911 ALL day & believe me we are blazing the roads all day to and from the hospital. & I know if I need a pick me up I will only stop at this location. They know how to get my coffee fix prompt and exactly how I like it. 90% of the time they see me pull up on the ambulance and they already have my order going before I make it in the store! I know they have to be tired of seeing me but they always greet me with a smile on their faces! I couldn’t ask for better service and great personalities!  It’s the “Be safe out there today.” For me! 🥲 Y’all are just as essential as I am and I thank y’all for your service!  & keep being great!☺️

With much love always!💕☕️

- a very great full EMT🚑💙

I make a habit of sampling any scones I can get my hands on and I'll gladly tell you these were some of the best I havr ever had. We ended up wanting to try one of every flavor because the first one was so good; and when the owner found out we were from out of town he sweetly made two of them on the house! Everything was scrumptious but my favorite flavor was the hazelnut cream. Simply Delightful! If I could go back I would, daily!

name: Lara Seamon
text:
Very pleased with every visit to Highland Gourmet Scones. I live out of the state and any time that I am in town I swing by for a scone pick up. I at first tried the mini's to distinguish which ones would be our favorite, but I have to be honest we like them all.

So we have upgraded to purchasing the large scones in a variety of flavors. A few have made it to being a fan favorite - Cherry Amaretto, Pumpkin Spice, Toasted Coconut, and Orange Cranberry. The regular size scones are a bit more moist, and have a stronger flavor.

We highly recommend them, and have not been disappointed with any of our orders!! The one time I returned home without scones..........we had a few sad faces. It is now what we look forward to when I am in town.

Plus they are a great spot for coffee!!

text: This is one of my favorite places. The Foyer brews their coffee from local downtown coffee shop, the Kaffeeklatsch. They make delicious specialty cheesecakes and have fair prices. Every Wednesday is open mic night and every Friday The Foyer brings in talented musicians from all over to play. The atmosphere is casual and relaxing and there's plenty of room to play board games or work on homework; free wifi! It's now open from 7am - 1am Monday through Saturday; closed Sundays. This is a fantastic place and locally owned and operated by fantastic and friendly people!

I stopped by here on Easter Sunday and was completely unaware of the early closing time. I arrived just as the lone barista was closing up shop. Still, the man was happy to take my order and was patient with me as I browsed the menu.

I ordered a chicken lunch croissant sandwich and an iced lavender and basil coffee and they were both absolutely delicious. The sandwich was very tasty and came with vegetable chips - never tried them before but I actually really liked them. I was a bit afraid to try the coffee, but it was just what I needed and I was surprised to see how good of a mix it was. Definitely coming back here again next time I'm in Uptown.

name: Megan Phillips
text:
Adorable! Love!
Free wifi for customers.
Comfortable seating and plenty of plugs for laptops.
Staff were super friendly and attentive.
I worked out of this shop for two days and during that time, I tried:
1. Hot chocolate-- First off, let me say, they used milk in the hot chocolate. This may seem like a small detail, but a disturbing number of coffee shops use water in their hot chocolate and that is not okay. Not Santos. Santos put milk in the hot chocolate like they care. I appreciate that. 10/10. Would order again.
2. Cold brew--The cold brew was good and would be great if you are a fast drinker, but it came in one of those clear cups that have no insulation, so if you are like me and leisurely sipping for an hour or so, the ice will melt and the cup will sweat. Not my favorite. 4/10.
3. Cafe Nutella--yaaaaasssss. This was by far my favorite. I absolutely loved it. Normally, I would have tried more items, but I ended up just getting this drink again because it was that good. 10/10. Would order again.

name: Richard Wallach
text: It’s 4:00 on Saturday, March 20th.  One employee working named Ruby who is definitely not a people person.  I’ve had less than stellar service at many establishments throughout the years,, but I’ve never had an employee literally roll her eyes when people gave their orders.  You work in a coffee place that sells smoothies and food.  Everyone is not going to order black coffee.  Maybe just a bad day for her, but don’t roll your eyes at the people who throw extra money in your tip jar.

text: Dangerous!! Update, and response to owner***The coffee shop has closed down, but instead of notifying Google, and thanking their patrons by adding a notification to the phone number, they surrounded the property with dangerous dogs. They are VERY AGGRESSIVE! Please do not try to park in the lot or you might be bitten. If they don't rectify this situation I foresee a lawsuit in the near future. Update:  The closed sign can NOT be seen over the truck parked in the lot if you are pulling in from the double springs side. Regardless. Most people are looking for parking not for a closed sign before pulling in. I'd like to know how many places of business you go to that you circle looking for closed signs before heading to the parking lot. Google says you were open. You can update that, and you have the responsibility to. My young daughter was almost bitten by your dangerous dogs. Unfortunately, you won't have my business again. It is not acceptable to claim you are trying to protect patrons by getting them bitten by your dogs. If you can't update review sites with proper information, then your patrons will. Put up a barrier across the lot if you want to ensure people don't enter. You're not trying to keep out invaders. You're trying to protect future patrons. Act like it.

resp.text: The Coffee House is currently under renovations and is closed - Temporarily. Please abide by our prominently displayed CLOSED sign. There are many construction projects currently ongoing and we are not open to the public to ensure their safety.
