I had no idea this particular location was "cards only" and all I had on me was some cash in my pocket (I left my wallet in my husband's car) so the cashier, without saying anything, paid for my order! That's the sweetest thing someone has ever done for me! Thank you, Starbucks!!

name: Sarah Dixon
text: It's a busy place and no drive though but did a good job

name: Helen H. Gonzalez
text: Nice Library. A lot of references that can be used for research. A clean and quiet place. They have places for a single person and for group of people to study in. I highly recommend this library for students to spend more time in.

name: Dylan Daughety
text: This review is only long due to the 200 character bonus points you get for each review. Really, this review should be one word, but why would I do that to you. You want details and information that will sell you this Starbucks and no other. Well I can't offer that information and I can't convince to come here. It is Starbucks and it is good. Thank you for your time.

name: Khayly V
text: I come often and there’s small issues here and there but forgiving because i see that it’s always busy and I know the workers are stressed out. Today everyone was sweet up until I received my drink from the barista. She looked like she hated her job, working at her own pace (meanwhile the line is backed up and the other workers are doing multiple orders) and when she finally finishes my drink she looks at the name and scoffed and mumbles under her breath “I’m not even going to try this” and said softly the name of the drink and as she continued to make someone else’s drink, the customer was watching her and had to correct her on her own order of how to make it! So I know it was not in my head about her attitude.  If I wasn’t sitting just right there in front of her I wouldn’t have heard any of that or my order and would’ve just been waiting and have had to assume If that was my order or not. Still a good rating just a rant review

name: Aint It Chief
text: That was amazing perfect for in between classes and a problem solver for a bad start to your day

name: Sarah Armstrong
text: Everyone here works really hard and they get your drinks out quick

name: Th3r3albooboo_kitty A.K.A undiscovered
text: I do not agree with whoever is managing this place I had a coupon for a free drink with my Starbucks rewards and was told i could not use it. I understand this location has the opportunity to be on campus good for them but that does not mean become a money sink. The employees are almost always brand new for a chill vibe go to springhill instead.

name: tobias pugh
text: Pretty nice atmosphere. Good tasting food

name: Constance McGlasker
text: I love Starbucks seasonal Smores Frappuccino, Caramel Frappuccino, and Strawberry Lemonade Refresher!

name: Chastity Touchstone
text: I had an 8am meeting on campus. I decided to go to the Starbucks on campus for my morning coffee instead of driving around mobile to get to one. The sign outside the door of this Starbucks (which is inside the library) said Friday 7:30-3:30. I walked in at 7:29 and they told me they weren't open yet. I walked out and waited. I went back in at 7:33 and they ignored me  until I walked up to the counter to order and then I was told we don't open until 7:45!!! I said, "the sign says 7:30" Then she says, we haven't changed it yet.....Now, because I waited on you to open at 7:30 LIKE THE SIGN SAYS!!! I have no time for coffee. You suck. And thanks for being so rude.

name: Tim Allen
text: The staff was very accomodating with my special request & thought outside of the box to accomplish it.

name: Mazen Omar
text: Good place to study. The employees are nice.

name: Justin Walker
text: Best Starbucks in the city!!!

name: Junya Winston
text: didn't like me or other blacks

name: Kayla Hollis
text: I go there daily to study and I absolutely love the employees. I never had a complaint.

name: Peanut Butter
text: It was the best experience you get kind service you get your coffee very fast 👍👍👍👍👍👍

name: Jean T Kiwiet
text: Love it, I am a regular and they alway make my drink right.

name: Dorothy Hill
text: Reason I am giving a 1 star is because I was charged 28 cents for ice. In my opinion ice should be free. I'll get my ice somewhere else from here on out.

name: Stefan Morris
text: Good clean environment! Quality service

name: Nancy Pugh
text: Haven't been there. Don't ever intend to go.

name: LOTR pottergirl
text: Small starbucks. Friendly staff. Fast.

name: jordan west
text: Expensive as usual but great service

name: Addam Smith
text: Staff works hard

name: Walter Randall
text: This place is, quite literally, a Starbucks.

name: i4Eric
text: Bruh.

name: Savannah Jones
text: I'm very picky about breakfast burritos, and most places get them too greasy and falling apart. But the burrito I had here they toast it like a panini so it doesn't fall apart and it was the best tasting burrito! Sausage, cheese, egg, onions, peppers. I asked for extra cheese and a cup of salsa. Best breakfast I've had in awhile. And it was more than enough, I was worried about not having a side but I couldn't even finish my burrito.

resp.text: We are so glad you enjoyed it! Come see us again soon!

name: Christine Wise
text: Great food, staff and atmosphere. We just discovered this place and have already visited it twice this week. Cheddar biscuits, chicken salad, fried pies all really yummy food. Can't wait to go back and try more stuff on the menu.

name: Kim Story
text: On a whim, I stopped here today to eat lunch. I got the strawberry and pecan salad (which came with an awesome dressing btw) ,and a fried apple pie. It was delicious!!! Will definitely be going back!

name: Jillian Wright
text: Hands down the best place in Arab- or even nearby- to get fried mushrooms. They are the only place that makes them just right!

name: Pam B
text: Delicious food! Very friendly staff with great service!

name: Ann Wright
text: Food was great. Staff friendly and attentive. Perfect spot for breakfast or lunch.

name: susan WING
text: I was so excited to finally be able to stop at the Station Cafe but now I  wish I had never made that stop. I ordered a large hot latte but what I got I have no idea. It was the worst latte I'd ever had. At first I thought it was just weak coffee and the guy just forgot what I ordered but I'm  not sure if it was even that. It was frothy so he got the milk part right I just don't know about the rest of it.  I did think at the time he made it awfully quick and I commented on that to him after all a 2 shot espresso latte takes a few minutes to make. I guess he must of just left out my 2 shots. Waste of $4.  I would have return to cafe but I  was almost home before I tried the drnk and I don't live in Arab.

resp.text: I’m so sorry that you didn’t enjoy your coffee! The gentleman that made your coffee today has many years of experience as a barista and since our opening in May, we’ve  had nothing but positive feedback on anything he’s made. Next time you are in town, we’ll be happy to refund your coffee or make you another one on the house! Again, I’m terribly sorry you didn’t enjoy your experience and we’d love the opportunity to try again!

name: Ivan Croes
text: Great options! Food is delicious!

name: Ducky
text: Absolutely loved it! The food was great and so was the coffee! Wish there had been a little more atmosphere. Some music or something playing would be great!

name: Jeremy K
text:
Excellent breakfast and a reasonable price.
Best sweet treats around. And its locally owned.   Well done Guy's.

name: Stephen Bearden
text: Fantastic coffee! Burgers were delicious!!

name: Malcolm Parsons (KI4KI)
text: Good food, good service, great atmosphere.

name: BulldogReddog
text: BEST COFFEE, I’ve drunk lots of coffee around the place but this is the easily the best for the best price 10/10 the worst part is finishing my coffee

resp.text: Thank you so much for your feedback. We hope to see you again soon!

name: Michael Cobb
text: Excellent food. The service was impeccable. Prices are very reasonable.

resp.text: Thank you for taking the time to leave your feedback. We value your business.

name: Ken Priest
text: Just went in to check it out

name: Pocket Bear
text: Food needs help

name: Andra Rutherford
text: Delicious food, great atmosphere, and excellent service!

resp.text: Thank you for leaving your review for our business.

name: Matthew Mabrey
text:
Delicious light-roasted . Visited twice during our week-long stay. The Bushwacker blend has incredibly flavorful berry notes that especially come out when you mix with sweet cream flavored creamer.

I normally drink my coffee straight but at the roasters recommendation I tried the Bushwacker with cream and it was delicious.

16 oz drip was $2.89
Bag of 1 lb beans was $13 ( ended up buying a bag for the rest of the week).

Tables outside and inside for use.
If you are particular about coffee, this is your spot!

name: Jennifer Seal
text: Loved our coffee from here. A local coffee shop that roasts their own beans. Great place and cute shop.

name: Honor Warren
text: I had the Salted Caramel Frappe and my daughter had a Caramel Mocha one. Both were delicious and the staff was super friendly. 10/10 recommend!

name: Leah Holland
text: Ok! Just left and will be back tomorrow! I never ever leave reviews, but felt I should because it’s soooo yummm! People were waiting so I quickly ordered my go-to caramel macchiato, which is delicious. I noticed the Bushwacker on way out and the super nice guy came over and gave me a sample with sweet cream.  Ummmm so good! So smooth, so fresh, so distinct! I’ll be back! Now sippin it on the beach. Thanks for perfection and making my day start off great! Simple joys you all provide!

name: Ed B
text: Great coffee! Sending someone from Missouri to pick up some more!

name: Adam Baldy
text: Friendly service and truly excellent breakfast sandwiches. Coffee was great as it should be.

name: Cole Schimek
text: Some of the BEST coffee I’ve had in the South! I’m from Minnesota and I like a good strong coffee and this is the BEST!! It’s awesome that he does everything by himself from getting green Coffee beans to putting it in the cup for you to drink!! Highly recommended!!!!!!

name: CausIsaid
text: Great selection. Tasty treats. Little pricey but it’s an island coffee shop. Friendly staff. Good afternoon picker upper!

name: Floyd Bakos
text: I prefer my drinks naturally flavor and sweetened. They're definitely not the one I am looking for. Mung bean milk tea is premixed which means sugar level not adjustable. Panden flavor and color are pretty artificial. It's loaded of sugar, I couldn't finished 1/4 of it. 3 stars is for the service. I drove back and got my refund promptly.

resp.text: I believe that you have the wrong restaurant. We’ve never had any type of milk teas on our menu. Please remove this review.

name: Rickey Garris
text: I'm not sure what I was more excited about...finally trying the birthday cake latte, or realizing that they sold mochi muffins here! I wanted to order one of everything but decided on the cookie butter latte, since my boyfriend ordered the birthday cake latte.

name: Cindy Mindy
text: Best coffee I have ever had in my life!!! This is a life changing experience! You must try the Cuban Latte.... WOW!  I even got to see Mark roast some of the coffee right there in his shop. This is by far the best coffee shop and my new go to when visiting Gulf Shores. I will need to stop by the Foley location on my next trip.

name: Shana Bell
text: Excellent coffee and service. The bushwhacker coffee is roasted in-house and delicious! Can buy bags in the store.

name: Joel Martin
text: Neat local coffee roaster. Friendly owner, and most importantly, smooth tasty coffee.

name: Mary Gray
text: Incredible people and super welcoming shop. I love coming here with my husband and my kids. They are super friendly and always happy to answer any questions. Used to be a die hard fan of a huge coffee chain, but since coming here I can’t wait to come back!! Amazing coffee, amazing atmosphere, amazing people, and amazing food!

name: Joshua Dinkins
text: Excellent French press coffee. Fresh roasted beans and knowledgeable staff. Thanks!

name: J
text: I discovered this beautiful coffee haven from Ciara, a very sweet employee from the hotel that I was staying at on business. It was an hour wait in the drive thru a few days after hurricane Sally hit the area. Yes, I waited that long. Let me reassure you that it was worth the wait!! It was my first time experience so I had questions. Even with the growing line behind me, Mary was so patient and kind with me. She made me the most delicious coffee that kept me coming back the entire 2 weeks I was in Foley! Thank you to the kind ladies of Southern Shores Coffee House for making my stay so very memorable! I'll be back!!!!

name: DC Home
text: Simply the best! the best service, coffee and pastries in the gulf area! treat yourself to a bushwhacker and a muffin in the morning! the coffee is fresh brewed and the pastries are home made! you won't be disappointed at either location!

name: Megan King
text: This place is absolutely incredible!!! My dad owned a coffee shop when I was younger and roasted his own beans in store which created some of the best quality coffee you could imagine. The first sip I took immediately took me back to my younger years at my dads cafe. The BEST quality coffee!! If you are ever in Gulf Shores, you have got to make this your coffee spot! You will be disappointed if you go anywhere else!!

name: Bodie Bachelor
text: Mark fresh roasts his coffee right in the shop. He makes all his own blends from green coffee grown all over the world. He has a first class Astori espresso machine & is well skilled in steaming milk for quality micro foam. The store is spotlessly clean & definitely beach themed. He went to great lengths to make sure our drinks were just right & definitely wants to please his customers. He also offers free samples of his Bushwhacker brew, which is very tasty!

name: Ruby Anderson
text: Favorite coffee in the city! And cute friendly little staff. Always pleasant and chirpy. Great to see in the morning.

name: LovelyLiddy
text:
Smoothest, best tasting coffee in Foley, hands down! Delicious house-made foods desserts, New York bagels (Their bagel sandwiches are awesome!) and macaroons straight from France.

The owners are kind, personable and open to their customers’ comments. Mark sources his beans selectively and roasts them himself at their Gulf Shores location across from Hope’s Cheesecake and his genuine passion for the craft of coffee is very apparent in the products they serve and produce.

They also have a drive-thru if you don’t want to go inside, but you should... they have a pool table and great A/C.

name: Rick Goldsworthy
text: Southern Shores is THE place to go to get a variety of locally roasted beans. Not beans roasted elsewhere and packaged for the shop (aka "private label"--which Southern Shores Coffee will do for other places). The couple I tried were solid. Note, I am not an added-flavor guy so I have no idea how any of the flavored roasts would be -- why would you do that to coffee! JK, to each his (or her) own. There are other great places in the area if you are wanting more of the cafe vibe (or gelato, more food choices, or a cuter atmosphere) but for coffee beans and great coffee, grab beans here. I tried the drip, which was good. Cannot comment on espresso base this time around so will need a return trip for that. Also, Finger Lickin' Good donuts is right next door, so you can't go wrong!

name: Hanna Slaughter
text: Super flavorful dark roast cold brew. The decor is amazing and very well designed. Service was amazing and the owners were very nice! They roast and infuse their own coffee beans and ship all over. Will definitely be coming back when we are back in town. Clean restrooms and access to a parking lot with no stairs. They also have their own roaster and dairy alternatives like almond and coconut milk! They were even able to make a decaf espresso for my mom! Definitely a great place to stop by for great coffee and friendly vibes!

resp.text: Thank you for your thorough review.

name: Jon Junkin
text: Great coffee and the hard-working owner is happy to talk shop and share his insights. I’ll be back for some more samples and to try their breakfast burritos/other breakfast offers!

name: Fink Condo Rentals LLC
text: Sweet people. Coffe is great. Many different choices and flavors. They roast onsite and have samples for you to try. We've needed a coffee shop on the island and this is great!

resp.text: Thanks so much for the review and the pictures added to google. Hope to see you again soon.

name: Montrea Posey
text: Delicious coffee- amazing people!

name: William Wright
text: Infused flavor coffee! It’s amazing you have to try the bushwhacker infused iced coffee! Also has a very nice patio to enjoy your beverage. Mins from the beach!

name: DeAnn Telarico
text: The Cuban Latte is addictive.  The owners of this shop are so nice and food and coffee are delicious.

name: manuel conde
text: The worst coffee. I just got the Bushwacher and it tasted awful. Don't waste your money. Maybe they can show me how to make it to tast like a Bushwacher. There was no paper in the box. That was misleading. I will ship it back to you. You should have disclaimer.

resp.text: While everyone has different tastes, yours is the first complaint that we’ve ever had on Bushwacker coffee. There should’ve been a paper in the box that shows which creamer to add to the Bushwacker. Ice cream cannot be roasted into coffee so we roasted the coffee to the creamer, just a little of the creamer and the coffee will taste just like the Bushwacker cocktail.

name: Katie Tackett
text: I love coming to this coffee shop every time I come to Gulf Shores!! The workers are so sweet and I always feel so welcomed when I visit. The coffee taste amazing and I even buy bags of coffee to take home with me! 100% recommend visiting this cozy coffee shop!

name: Candace Graves
text: Excellent coffee! We had a great experience! The owner is friendly and knowledgeable. He even had coffee out to sample before we made our decisions.  We will definitely be return customers on our next trip down.

name: Jennifer Reid
text: My daughter and I got lattes on our way out of town. They were delicious and we heard another gentleman telling the barista that His chi drink was the best he’d ever had.  Don’t miss this out of the way coffee shop. Egg, sausage burrito was good too.

name: Chloe Carlisle
text: very friendly staff! great iced coffee & nitro cold brew with an awesome breakfast selection. best of all— very cheap!

name: Bryan W. Rowe
text: This small business does their own blending, roasting and grinding in-house. Wonderful people and coffee with many great house blends!!

name: Brian Hampton
text: The atmosphere is super chill and definitely represents the beach life. The smiles are contagious and the customer service is excellent. What about the coffee? THE COFFEE IS 🔥🔥🔥🔥

name: Pamela May
text: Southern Shores Coffee is a delight to have in the Foley area....fresh coffee, delicious treats and a soothing atmosphere... not to mention all the beautiful blondes ready to serve up the best coffees in Foley!!

name: Bre Sullivan
text: Good coffee, good prices. The owner is very friendly and knows his stuff about roasting coffee. This was a great stop on our vacation. The birthday cake coffee is the best coffee I’ve ever had in my life. More like a dessert!

name: Renea Eyman
text:
My favorite all vegan treats. There are few places that have such a variety of exquisite delights as this place. This is a fun and interesting atmosphere, friendly yet creatively punk hip workers will answer any question.  This place has it all.
Southern Shores Coffee.

name: Nancy Smith
text: Sweet baristas, very helpful!!

name: Hawk1
text: Excellent service and products. My kids got a real kick out of the cutely decorated frappes!

name: Francesca Esposito
text: It was amazing! The peach tea was amazing and I loved the cheesecake! 100/100 service :)

name: Blade Gray
text: This place is awesome, so many drink choices and homemade whipped cream! Love the people, love the environment!!

name: Pep Whirley
text: Loved it. Great coffee friendly service. Can’t wait to go back for more!

name: Chrissie Hesser
text: Amazing options! Love this place! Family operated and so welcoming to Thier patrons.

name: Mic Reul
text: Best coffee around.   He is the only roaster on the island and is very knowledgable about the coffee.  Mark and his staff are friendly and greet everyone with a smile

name: Blyn Vyborny
text: Delicious coffee and deserts. Great afternoon pick me up.

name: Eliana Vercellino
text: We were stranded just minutes on our trip back to TN. Luckily we pulled into this place and across from Advanced auto. They were super kind to us. We had coffee and food. Took 3 hours to get our car up and running. But this experience couldn’t have been better thanks to this place!!!

name: Bob Bross
text: Super cute and owner is really friendly.

name: Rose Strotman
text: Best place ever for coffee and small bites. Homemade & propriety coffees hot & cold. Amazing service. Family owned. Awesome cinnamon rolls made fresh daily. Home of the Famous Bushwhacker coffee also roasted daily. Nice sandwiches and breakfast items.

name: Blade Gray
text: This place is awesome, so many drink choices and homemade whipped cream! Love the people, love the environment!!

name: Blyn Vyborny
text: Delicious coffee and deserts. Great afternoon pick me up.

name: David Gomez
text: This place has a really nice atmosphere, friendly staff, good food and great coffee.

name: Brandy K
text: Cute, charming and delicious

name: Michael Jenkins
text: I love this little coffee shop, and go there often. So many varieties of coffee roasted in house. And the local owners are genuinely nice people!  Stop in for a cup and be sure to take a bag or two for home. Our friends love getting them as gifts!!

resp.text: Thank you Michael.

name: Amber Davis
text: Excellent coffee

name: Jackson Chism
text: Wanted to surprise my wife with coffee from a local shop while we were on vacation. Stopped in and asked the owner (I’m assuming) for recommendations on what to get her. Got home with the coffee he recommended, and my wife absolutely loved it! Great coffee and great people!

resp.text: I’m so glad to hear that your wife liked her drink. Thank you for the great review!

name: Michelle R.
text: We were on the hunt for coffee and found this great place. My husband always drinks an Americano and said his was delicious.  I tried the Cuban latte and found it amazing.  We both had a breakfast burrito - again, so delicious! The proprietors were very welcoming, and it was clearly a place the locals frequent.  They roast their beans on site.  We will be back.

name: Matt Koon
text: Love this local coffee shop! Get the bushwacker coffee!

resp.text: Thank you for the great review Matt. It was great to meet you.

name: Amy Henschen
text: I'm baffled by the good reviews for this place. Ordered a pour over and flat white. No one was waiting for drinks when we got there and they had 2 staff members, yet the flat white took 10 minutes and the pour over 15. Both were mediocre at best. Do not recommend.

resp.text:
I apologize for your experience. In reviewing this situation the pour over you ordered was done in an 8 cup Chemex which takes roughly 10-11 minutes with prep time start to finish. The coffee used was a light roast Ethiopian  yirgacheffe. The Yirgacheffe may not have been the coffee you as it is a light roast with a citrus note.
Please reach out to us via Facebook, email or phone 251-442-5415 as we would like the opportunity to correct this for you.

name: Wendi Kinsey
text: Hidden gem! Cute cozy quite place to just sit and enjoy a cup of joe!

name: Sharon Phillips
text: Amazing Bushwacker coffee!!! Locally owned!!! ❤❤❤❤

name: Enos Henderson
text: Great!!!!! Service.   Just show up and you’ll see. Oh yeah coffee pretty darn good too!!!

name: Gay Ann Bakker
text: Good customer service

name: Hollie Palmer
text: Absolutely delicious coffee! I ordered a hot mocha and I was not disappointed! Even my husband, who dislikes the "coffee" taste of coffee said it was good! If you're debating between the sizes of cups, do yourself a favor and get the bigger size! You will not regret it. I would definitely reccomend this place to anyone looking for some coffee in Gulf Shores!

name: Rusty Newton
text:
Friendly service, delicious breakfast sliders and robust flavorful coffee. Nice outdoor seating area if the weather is good. Affordable prices on top of all that!

I'm only here on vacation, but if I'm in the area again I'll be back!

name: Tommy Braggs
text: The chicken salad croissant is AMAZING!

name: Stephanie Baldridge
text: We came sliding in at 4:00 and he stayed open so we could get our coffee fix. Coffee was fabulous! Great conversation, great place! Thank you

resp.text: Thank you for the great review. I enjoyed meeting you and your family, we hope you have a great time while you are in town.

name: Amelie Thomas
text: Very nice and sweet people here and the coffee and food selection is more diverse than a normal coffee shop and not to mention tastes good too. Thanks for the caffeine.

name: Savanna Tays
text: Loved this place. The owner was very nice

name: Nicole Miller
text: If you’ve been looking for excellent coffee, look no further! We were visiting from Dayton, Ohio and found this gem (thank God for the coupon book at Rouse’s market). You MUST try the Bushwacker coffee (Mark’s trademarked flavor)...Hot is fantastic and the cold brew of it is even better! We went back 3 times and got extra cups of coffee to go for early beach walks the next morning....that’s how much we loved it. Also tried a Mocha with caramel and the frozen sea salt caramel, both of which were legit. Bought some whole beans and can’t wait to relive this taste of paradise when we get home. Mail order beans here we come! Thanks Mark for the enriching experience and thanks Mark’s wife for your dedication and contributions of which Mark spoke so highly!

resp.text: Thank you for the great review Nicole. It was great to meet you both, we look forward to seeing you on your next trip down.

name: Robert Orr
text: Great coffee and service. Owner very friendly. Lady working the cash register is super nice.

name: Priscilla Russell
text:
Best coffee shop around, and a game changer for the veg scene. Everything is delicious and well made, place is beautiful, and there is now twice as much seating.
Southern Shores Coffee.

name: Kaela
text: I just had the best pumpkin latte I've ever had.

name: Ashley Johnson
text: The best coffee on the beach! The service is always amazing and the atmosphere is perfect.

name: Pam Carson
text:
Mixed smooth, cold brewed coffee with Almondmilk, best ice coffee in a long time, fresh-baked peanut butter chocolate chip cookie hit-every note.
Southern Shores Coffee.

name: Kath Katherine
text: Such an awesome find on Piedmont Ave.  TImeless serves up excellent pour over coffee and espresso drinks all while maintaining veganism throughout the process.

name: jj liebel
text: It's not hard to find a decent cup of coffee down in gulf shores but if you're looking for exceptionally good flavorful fresh roasted indulgent coffee this is a must go to if to just try there Bushwacker and blueberrie roast.  Luv this place and the Cuban latte was exactly what I needed.  Thank you

name: Amber Fieck
text: Stopped here on our way back home from a beach vacation in Gulf Shores. I WISH I HAD DISCOVERED IT SOONER! I would have been here every single day of my trip! Superb coffee and espresso beverages, amazing service, very clean, and an inviting beachy atmosphere. Well worth a stop!

name: Matt Koon
text: Love this local coffee shop! Get the bushwacker coffee!

resp.text: Thank you for the great review Matt. It was great to meet you.

name: Maria Jimenez
text: Cute place, very friendly, delicious coffee 👍🏼

name: Bailey Whitcomb
text: We visited this coffee shop while on vacation! We ended up coming back every morning because it was so good. Very clean and amazing customer service.

resp.text: Thank you for the great review Bailey. We appreciate it.

name: Hoffmann Rexhaku
text:
This place great coffee simple is European
I love this coffee great owner thanks for coffee🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

resp.text: Thank you for the great review.

name: Emily Carrico
text: Our cycling team stopped by on a ride to grab some drinks and food. The man working was super friendly, brewed fresh decaf coffee for us, and gave us an extra tea for free! Even more, he filled our water bottles for us, without us even asking. Super friendly service and delicious coffee!

resp.text: Thank you for the great review.

name: Chuck n Peg Allen
text: Found this southern gem and can't wait for tomorrow morning to get some more. The owner is very knowledgeable and conscientious about what he brings to your table. A real delight to find!

resp.text: It was great to meet you, we are looking forward to seeing you again tomorrow. Thank you so much for the great review.

name: Beverly M2017
text: Was in town for Hangout Fest, my friends and I came across this coffee shop gem! Great customer service and coffee! If you love legit coffee and are in the area, it's a must stop place to get your fix!

name: sheila reul
text: Best coffee around. Love the owners and their  knowledge  of coffee.  Not to mention the only roasters on the Island.

name: Adam Hochstedler
text: Awesome coffee shop! We were in town for vacation and found this gem the first day. I assume we will be here several times while in Gulf Shores. Thanks for the great service and coffee!

name: Wes Ludloff
text: Decent place, good cold brew and friendly service.  Menu is written on a dry erase board and a bit hard to read...maybe use bigger lettering when you change menu items.  Will be back!

name: Elaine Mcmurray
text: Amazing coffee shop!!!!!!!   Amazing delicious coffee!  Owner roasts coffee beans inhouse!!!!!!   Now I need to get them to move to Michigan...😏

name: Bethany Lee
text: Great customer service and pretty excited that they carry whole coffee beans. Thanks!

name: Penny G.
text:
Saw it on face book, thanks to Jim Parks, our neighbor and went by this morning after a beach stroll.  Very artsy upscale shop who roasts their coffee and ships nationally as well as provides a variety of breakfast items, sliders, letc., and a hefty variety of specialty coffee beverages! Samples offered!!!
So excited to do business with a convenient Local rather than traveling further to buy from the other large national Chain💥. A must try if you Love coffee.  Stop by and get to know Heather and Mark☕️☕️☕️☕️😎

resp.text: It was great meeting you, thank you for the feedback. We look forward to seeing you again.

name: Kylee Engleman
text: So happy that we found this place!!! Great coffee & hot chocolate. We had a wonderful experience with friendly service. Will definitely be back!

name: Leah McLaughlin

text:
The employees at this McDonald’s are fantastic, but the upper management/Ownership of this McDonald’s is severely lacking. This location is always understaffed. Equipment from the credit card machines to drive thru speakers are the worst of every McDonalds I have ever been to.

Today the drive thru is wrapped around the building decided to go inside, every customer inside was mad with the line and the orders that were wrong and the fact that it appeared to be only 2 employees trying to deal with a disaster.

Last item the side door by drive through was locked, I would think that would be a Fire Marshall violation.

As I was writing this notice a long time employee working extremely hard and deserves a Gold Medal for her service, the fact that she does not walk off the job is an incredible testimony to her incredible work ethic. Lucy you get 5 Stars!

I left and came back 30-40 minutes later and was told the ice cream machine was down.  That happens A Lot.  What I'm guessing is that they clean it and do not want to get it dirty again so they do not have to clean it again when they close.  It is always being cleaned or down.

Dirty.  Look around the fountain drink machines and it is nasty.

This McDonald's used to be top notch and the service was great.  But for a long time now it has been so bad that I try my best to go elsewhere if I have time.

Then we proceeded to wait in line for 20 minutes. We paid, then pulled up to the receive window and it took a hot second for them to give us our food, but we got it. I looked in the bag and saw a portion of our order was missing, so we turned around and I went in store. The main cashier was super nice, I was very happy with that, and of no fault of hers, the orders we failing to come out properly and in a timely manner. There were a couple gentlemen in front of me when I initially went in store, they also failed to receive their full order as well. The cashier up front requested another order of chicken nuggets (what I was missing) and she told me it was going to be about 3-5 minutes. So I continued to wait. And wait. And wait. Then another 15 minutes went by all while people who came in well after I did ordered 3 separate orders of what I had been waiting for. So. I left. Terrible back service. The lady up front was sweet and for the most part accommodating, she came after me when I left and pleaded to help, but I just wanted to go home and I’m still 4 hours from home.

I like McDonald's generally, but this experience has been my worst. I look forward to them getting better employees and implementing a better ordering system (as well as improving on the food I used to love growing up), until then I would recommend going to Burger King or Chick-fil-A.

Nice little coffee shop with very happy employees with coffee that makes you Peppy! Good sandwiches as well.
Decor inside is nice and very inviting.

text: Visited from Kentucky and stopped in right before they closed. They were super friendly and the coffee was delicious! Not only did they have a nice assortment of desserts, but they also had a gluten free option for me.

name: Melissa Francois
text: Great coffee and atmosphere. Inside and outside is adorable! Very friendly accommodating staff. They sold me matcha powder to use as a natural green dye for our St Patty's day pancakes!

name: Tanya Wallace
text: Great coffee, excellent muffin & cookies and the young man who waited on us was wonderful!

name: Joey Smith
text: In Gulf Shores for a 3 day stay. We stopped in the shop simply because of the name. My grandkids call me “Pappy” so I thought it’d be fun to go in, get a coffee and have my photo op with the “Happy Pappy“ sign. But I was very impressed with the service of the two young ladies that served us there. They were extremely busy when we were there so I was able to observe the efficiency of them, all done with smiles on their faces. My plan was to get their names so I could thank them personally on here but as stated earlier, they were busy. So, whomever was working on 12/29 at @ 9 AM, thank so much for your nice place and your great coffee! My wife and I are fans!

name: Jane Reynolds
text:
Some friends recommend this Cafe.  Our group kept growing, ended up with at least 15 people.   It was no problem for this small family restaurant.   Service was good and very friendly.
Food is great, soup and sandwiches and sweet rolls and oh yea coffee!

name: Carly Stuart
text: The staff was sooooo friendly and welcoming! The coffee and pastries were also a great start to our day for our trip back home :)

text: Great atmosphere. Staff was curteous, articulate, and a pleasure to be in company with. Great BEC for breakfast.

name: Simone Savoie
text: What a gem of a spot! Came here to do some work while waiting to meet up with a friend. Food is SO reasonably priced, I ordered a medium lavender white coffee and it was way bigger than I expected, flavor there but not overpowering or sickly sweet. Quiche was delicious, and the aromatic lemon muffin was absolutely delectable. Wish I lived here so I could be a regular.

name: Darcy Dunham
text: Happy Pappy's is, hands down, the BEST coffee shop I've ever visited (and I'm a coffee shop guru)! The staff is incredible, friendly, knowledgeable about their job duties etc. The place itself is CLEAN, decorated beautifully, cozy (they have tables with chairs, couches and bar style stool chairs by the window), great selection of food (pastries, quiche, sandwiches etc.), the owner is SO FRIENDLY! He made me and my Mother feel at home and took time out of his schedule to talk to us while we were there! I found that to be the greatest of customer service! We WILL be back SOON! Go here, you will love it!

name: Peter Gilman
text: This place is amazing. We came here once and had to return again and again on our week at the beach. The coffee is full flavored, the staff is friendly and helpful, the food delicious and the atmosphere enjoyable and relaxing. What more could you want?

text: Had the Tiramisu Cappuccino and it was outstanding! Don't know the guys name who was serving us but he was very hospitable.

name: Dan S
text:
Wanted to say that my wife and I tried out Happy Pappy's this past Saturday evening about 30 minutes before they closed. I had an Americano but my experience was completely the opposite of Tim McCabe's experience. My Americano was great, I drink it black and I was very impressed with the quality and taste of coffee (I absolutely hate Starbucks). My wife was on the phone and said choose something, so I chose a French vanilla latte for her. She later told me she's not usually a big fan of  French Vanilla lattes but she really liked hers because it still tasted like coffee. I will definitely be venturing back many times to come because a good cup of coffee isn't the easiest thing to come by. Their prices were very fair!

PS: Tim, go try them again!

name: Clifford Starke
text: Great experience. Friendly Barista and ample table space and outlets to study, work or chill out. Would come back.

name: Lara Oje
text: I absolutely love this place. Love the owner; he's so nice and down to earth and cares about people. This is my second visit and I don't know why it's taken me this long to try here. His niceness will definitely make me come back. Everything I have tried tastes amazing and I can't wait to keep trying them all. Thank you Sam for being a great human being. Everyone come visit!

name: Adrah Kooin
text: Amazing coffee, easy atmosphere, and great service. I am addicted to the coffee toffee pieces!!

name: Loaf Dog
text: Very quiet and well-handled atmosphere, great for studying or just taking a moment to relax (the chai tea is heavenly)

name: Mark Barber
text: In my opinion it’s the best coffee shop in Auburn. Opelika has sidetrack now finally Auburn has its own. The owner takes great care into everything that comes off the bar and is always working to offer different coffees on pour over and batch. It’s a great spot to come and sit and have your drink and settle and enjoy the atmosphere. Definitely support this place! If you like sweet coffee definitely try the toffee coffee and if you are a more straightforward coffee person I love the macchiato!

name: shraddha praharaj
text: Very quiet and serene place! Service is pretty good, and love the latte art!

name: Ms. T
text: I really enjoyed my visit here. Very clean store. Staff is friendly and very helpful. I will definitely be coming by again the next time I visit Auburn.

name: Audrey Butcher
text: Perfect matcha latte. Nice atmosphere. Definitely recommend.

name: Melissa Rey
text: This coffee shop is wonderful! The quality is amazing and definitely worth the price. The owner is a lovely person who makes sure the atmosphere is positive and provides excellent customer service. He goes the extra mile to ensure that all of his products are perfect and will make sure to fix any problems with your order. Definitely go!

name: Caleb Hunt
text:
Uniq Coffee is the best coffee shop in Auburn, AL. It truly is "Uniq" in every way.

Sam shows every customer top service and makes you instantly feel welcomed and at ease. The coffee is the best you can find from Prevail Union which originally started in Auburn. The drinks at Uniq are amazing and are wonderfully paired with HOMEMADE BAKED GOODS that Sam crafts and bakes himself–make sure to try the "Bean Bread"!

The folks at Uniq clearly have a knack for interior design because there is a sublime balance of modern and homey and with art from local artists, the vibe is complete (make sure to look for the Einstein ballin' with a pipe in his mouth cartoon).

I seriously can't recommend Uniq Coffee enough. Drink Uniq!

name: David Collins
text: Visited from out of town - it was a great spot!

name: Brad Caldwell
text: This place and Ross House are the two best coffee places in Auburn, without question. Amazing tasting espresso with plant milk options & real iced matchas. This is the real deal!

name: Caitlynn Darby
text: The yummiest coffee and baked goods! We love Sam (the owner/barista). He’s super friendly and has the greatest ideas for drinks. It’s a great place to have coffee with a friend or study while drinking some amazing coffee. We love visiting weekly. :)

name: Dalton Bright
text: Sam, the owner and main barista at Uniq, is a fantastic guy who has an evident passion about coffee. The cafe space also showcases his other passions of music and interior design. It is a lovely cafe with great local art on the walls. As far as the coffee goes, Sam truly knows what he is doing. Every drink he serves is great, regardless of what you may order. If you are in the Auburn area, I highly suggest checking out Uniq; you won't regret it.

name: Ellie Tartt
text: Best service ever! Always so nice and welcoming, we come here often to study and he knows our drinks now, hands down best coffee shop in Auburn.

name: Maddie Marsh
text: Amazing customer service, great quality coffee, and lots of seating. It's the perfect place to get work done or chill with friends. Sam (the owner) is so kind, one time he ordered everyone in the coffee shop pizza to give out for free. Great environment!

name: Ugarte Aurelia
text: Coffee was so rich and flavorful, the owner puts so much care into everything they do, and the music selection was top notch!

name: Trey Roach
text: The owner is such a kind spirited person, and the coffee is good. There is time, effort, and care put into those drinks, and there are interesting things on the menu for sure. I recommend everything they’ve got!

name: Curtis Bowden
text: Excellent cortado with almond milk! Creamy espresso and the almond milk was just right in flavor and amount. Highly recommended!

name: Mia Kirila
text: An amazing experience. Great signature drinks but the best part is Sam (the owner)! Extremely sweet and friendly- really makes sure the environment is welcoming and comfortable.

name: Fallen Kierkegaard
text: A clean aesthetic, a quality product, and a great atmosphere. Easily my favorite new coffee shop. If you want to study or meet up with a friend, this is the place to be.

name: A H
text: Great place to study. The workers are very friendly. They have toffee coffee that I really recommend it to try it.

name: Thina Biblis
text: Always good coffee and great service.

name: Tucker Strane
text: Great environment, great people, great coffee!

name: Victoria Zona
text: I absolutely love this coffee shop and is easily my new favorite in Auburn. The owner is so kind and the coffee is delicious! I am sad to be graduating and moving soon, but I know when I am back in Auburn I will definitely be stopping in.

name: J Walters
text: Awesome coffee and really chill atmosphere. Great place to sip a latte and study or chill

name: David Pugh
text: Great shop with exceptional coffee!

name: Lily Kirila
text: Best customer service!! The baristas are so friendly and very helpful in picking out drinks! Would definitely recommend!

name: jaimee Adams
text: A great spot, owned by recent young grad from Auburn, who is a fun-loving person.  Loved his green tea Macha latte and went back 3 times in 3 days for the strawberrybices latte!  The place is so cool, and chill.  He built the tables himself ans has a real eye for design.

name: AJ Ellison
text: Sam and Caleb are great and really know their stuff! The shop fills such a need in Auburn for a nice clean space with people who really know their coffee! By far my favorite coffee place in Auburn!

name: Chase Ledbetter
text: Extremely tasty and homey. Amazing customer service.

name: Kalyn Warren
text: Uniq is my favorite! Beautiful, comfortable, ample seating, wifi, and Sam is just a delightful business owner.

name: Chulki Kim
text: Everything is good but need more parking space

name: Hanna Ray Hardman
text: Chill atmosphere that's ideal for studying and good coffee. The Toffee Coffee comes with toffee pieces on top and was delicious. The service was great too. The barista was very friendly and even brought water to everyone's table without anyone asking.

name: Mattie Boy
text: Incredibly friendly people with great service. They offer all the basics but include some super unique flavors that exceeded my expectations

name: Rachel Lanier
text: My new favorite coffee spot in Auburn! Chill atmosphere, unique coffee, and amazing customer service!

name: Dalton Odom
text: Such friendly service. The baristas go out of their way to help each customer.

name: Jin Noh
text: Nice place and the coffee was good

name: Becky Williams
text: Hot cocoa was excellent

name: Timothy Blackmon
text: Toffee Coffee is awesome

name: Carey Bray
text: Wonderful!!

name: Jackie DeJesse
text:
Cute spot that’s just starting up! Had an iced cappuccino with a single shot with oat milk and it was 😋. FYI for half caf folks that they don’t serve decaf (hence my single shot!).

They also have a lovely shared patio to sit in which is perfect for spring/summer.

name: Mark Barber
text: Mannnnnnn. It’s hard to find good espresso. Texture and temp was perfect. Like a dang juice bomb. So good. Can’t wait til the brick and mortar to open. Great to have this place since Woodlawn was taken away (rip). Can’t wait to come back here!

name: Neil Adams
text: Best coffee in birmingham. Tim brews it better than anyone and that June Roasters coffee is always on point. Do yourself a favor and try it.

name: Mark Richardson
text: Great peaceful place to study with great lighting. No wifi at the moment but it helped me stay engaged in my reading. Tim, the barista, was very friendly. The espresso was not too bitter; it had just a hint of sweetness. The milk was frothed perfectly with a smooth consistency throughout and it was a great temperature, ready to drink fresh from the espresso machine. One of the best lattes in bham. I plan to make this place a regular

name: Drew Templeton
text: Always enjoy the coffee and getting to talk with Tim. Love the simplicity of the space and the beauty of the sitting area all around it.

name: Kiersten Mallory
text:
An excellent and needed addition to the Birmingham third wave coffee scene. Extremely knowledgeable and passionate about providing excellent craft coffee. Takes the time to know and customize orders to a patrons request. And not to mention a cheerful conversation to add to your day.
My personal favorite is an iced oat milk cappuccino :)

name: Caley Ellenburg
text: Such good coffee and Tim (owner) is always ready to have fun and friendly conversation! Best espresso in town. The seasonal flavors are delicious and hilariously named. Grateful for this little spot!

name: Laura Holland
text: Super cute, peaceful little spot serving the best coffee I’ve had in bham.

name: Your Local Stream of Consciousness
text: Okay food for what you pay for. Although my sandwich would have been better if it was actually on the bagel I’d ordered. And I hadn’t needed to repeat my coffee order (a large hot latte) 4 times.

name: Lauren Smith
text: Good food. Workers often forget your order though and screw it up. Past 3 times I've been there they get the bagel wrong and forget to double the eggs even thought I paid for it. Staff can be quite rude when this is pointed out so at this point I've just stopped ordering what I want and just grab whatever. Wish the manager could fix this but I rarely ever see him. Wish I could get my money back

name: Up is Down
text: Leander and the crew are excellent. Decent Food and the espresso is tough to beat.

name: wil cisneros
text: The bagels are great. The jalapeño is my favorite.

name: Bradley Barger
text: Conveniently located (for students) in the LRC building. Nearly inaccessible for others. Can be busy at lunch, and at the top of every hour when classes change. Prices and taste are good, but not notable. Staff are nice,  even when the line of customers stretches out the door.

name: Christian Mays
text: It is what it is. Quick bagels and food that is convenient but nothing to write home about. Can't complain. Very fast and pretty cheap for a bagel.

name: Matthew Pearson
text:
If you're a UAB student, just go here.. Skip Panera and Starbucks if you're looking for food. The sandwiches here are SO MUCH better than Panera. I mean in another league. And they cost less.

I have yet to try their coffee, but as they seem to serve caribou coffee, I am sure it will be more than adequate. I will be skipping Starbucks except when I am in the mood for a frappuccino.

YES it is worth the walk(not really far from anything anyways). Even better if you live in Blazer or NFR.

It may not be the absolute best food out there, but for UAB students with dining dollars? Best I've had. That is unless you want a burger.

tl;dr Best food I've had at UAB unless you're craving for a burger, then go the Den.

name: Carolyn Maddox
text: Kevin, is totally awesome. My order was huge, complex, correct and on-time!!!! #YouRock!!

We appreciate you being our customer!

text: How can you mess up a double cheeseburger and iced caramel coffee? You visit this location. One bright spot was the order/cash taker at the first window. Pleasant, smiled, too good for McDonalds. Only reason to visit again would be to see if the first time was just a fluke.

name: Anthony Dixon
text: Not impressed with the new chicken sandwich at all. Seems like the same old chicken sandwich they had before.

name: Victoria Brown
text: It's honestly hard to find a consistently good McDonald's though this location always give you, not only what you expect of fast food restaurant, but the foundation of a fast food restaurant. They are always,  fresh, and hot. I know most of us look forward to the long lost fries at the bottom of the bag, but they package everything so neatly that this fry stragglers are a thing of the past.

name: Jacob Chad
text: If your open 24/7 that should mean as such. Showing up and the lanes blocked off by those sexy cones was the highlight of my evening/morning...UPDATE YOUR HOURS ON GOOGLE so people dont waste time driving there!!!!!!

name: Raptor Jesus
text: I second the opinion I've seen a few times here on this review board, but with a catch. It's not just this location that does well; they do, but one employee in particular stands out. Saheed, the only employee working there at 10:30 PM on a Saturday night, was blazing through a line that wrapped around the building. Our order was perfect, fresh and ready at the window. Dealing with both drive-through and walk-in customers, this guy has got it HARD. Just a shining example of someone who deserves to do better in this society but is kept down by corporate greed and the stagnant minimum wage, notwithstanding exceptional effort and efficiency. I'll be coming back only because I know they can handle this.

name: Amber Terry
text: I visited this McDonald's today. I bought my baby a chicken nugget happy meal. My other kid a big mac. I had a caramel frappuccino and look what I saw... I'm very irate. That's why I always check my food and never eat in the dark. Be cautious. Be are.

name: Lilli _ann
text: On March 29 at 10:55  after waiting for 10 minutes at least my partner and I get to the speaker only to have them tell us they're closed. That's not what the time listed says. I'd leave 0 stars if I could. Based on other reviews the place has gone downhill. In general do not recommend this place at all

name: Randy aka xXClusterOneXx
text: This is usually our "go to" McDonald's. The food is always fresh and the service is fairly fast. All my orders have been correct. Not sure about the ice cream machine though.😉

name: Tanya Franklin
text: Ordered a large fry. Service was good but my fries were cold like they had been sitting. It was not busy and shortly before the lunch rush.

name: Arena Hill
text: i don’t understand why people still waste their money on mcdonalds, it’s disgusting not healthy at all and very rude employees all the time. especially this location one of the african american manager, lady got an attitude with me when i said the cinnamon roll is always hard & cold. and she said well we just microwave it that’s all! that’s why it’s hard & cold you have to eat it fast, and i was like sheesh in my mind this lady could of said nothing instead!!

name: Ardy Gee
text: During the day it's wonderful I give it five stars until about 8pm after 8 it seems like the milkshake machines always broken. everything's a lot slower. the people are a lot less friendly.  Don't get me wrong there not rude by any means just not quite as friendly. and the milkshake machine always being broken really ticks me off because I love my milkshakes...

name: Merrily Serota
text: Always happy with the service. Food is ready quickly even when special ordered! Great prices on meal deals!

name: Michael Norris
text:
Absolutely terrible. Before going to the hotel, we visited a little before 11pm on a Friday night. Sat in the drive through line forever. We decided to do a mobile order. Placed the order and marked it as inside pick up. Little did we know the doors were locked so we could not get in.

I wasn’t going to wait another 30 minutes in the drive through line only to move up one car spot. I tried calling several times to tell them to cancel the order. No answer. I’ve left voicemails after the “beep” which sounds like I should record a VM, but no phone calls back.

After reading some of the other reviews, looks like this place just 100% sucks.

name: Diquinda Mccrary
text: Delicious food. My meal was neatly prepared and served hot. This is my second time in one week ordering at this location . My drive thru order was prompt and I received friendly service from the drive thru server.

name: jeffery green
text: Shut this one down. Go thru the drive thru at midnight wait 10 minutes to order then pull around wait another 5 minutes for the food you ordered and pray you got the right food. The attitude of the employees are pathetic for fast food workers.

name: Beverly Crider
text: Out of sanitizer at both payment kiosks. After entering order at kiosk, I was notified the payment option was down and I would have to pay at counter. That should have been stated up front.

name: Cedric Mason
text: The quality of food ,correctness of orders ,and attitudes of workers has really went down again at this location

name: Harold Threatt
text: Always good service,I send my employees there all the time to get breakfast

name: Son of Hecate
text: A nice short wait when you order your food off the kiosk.

name: David Burrowes
text:
I usually go here for their hot fudge sundaes, but after this experience, I may need to rethink that. I pulled up at the drive through, and there were 2 cars in each lane.

After a few minutes of the line not moving, I decided to park and go inside. The manager was having a conversation with two customers about some mixup in their order. It took a few minutes to get that straightened out.

There was another customer ahead of me, and neither of us were ever acknowledged or spoken to. I decided to get back into the drive through. There were two cars in each lane again, and I got into the outside lane.

Well, the person managing the drive through sent two cars through for each one car in my lane.

Then, when I got to the first window, I had a tough time understanding the young man about how much I owed. I  proceeded to the second window, and I  got the sundaes, and I had asked for extra fudge sauce. It's usually put in on the top and the bottom. One sundae had it only on top, so I questioned the woman about that, and she said that it was extra, just on top.

It wasn't bad, but the service just seemed slow and inefficient. I'll give them the benefit of the doubt, as I believe they were understaffed.

name: Alan “AJ” Bredemann
text:
I can only review this place from the standpoint of an employee, since I were to pretend to be a customer my account would biased. Also note that this is my first retail job, so that probably affects my perception quite a bit.

In brief, it's a nice place to work; they pay well for entry level, provide flexible hours and good management. It's good work if you wish to pick up a job

On the downside, training is a bit sporadic as you are taught more the longer you work there, at the beginning it's easy to feel almost helpless in many situations. It's also very easy to get overwhelmed during rush hours, but usually things work out.

Overall, I dont think I could have asked for a better first job. I will certainly come back whenever I'm back in town.

She was rushing to take my order so obviously she didn’t hear that. When I paid and got my food, I asked nicely if my 4 sauces were in the bag. I’m very understanding if it’s forgotten since I’ve worked fast food before. She said there was only 2 in the bag and proceeded to charge me for 2 more. I was okay with paying. I got home only to find 2 sauces in the bag. So why would I get lied to and charged for 4? I should’ve checked myself. I’ll take my time and check the bag next time since I know I’ll probably be lied to. Giving 3 stars because I never have any problems here, and usually the cashiers double check for me and are nice about it. The cashier who handed me the food worked the shift May 6th around 5:00/5:30pm.

text:
Trip 1:
Sat in drive thru for Doordash order 23 minutes. This was after sitting in the online order/curbside pick up spot and trying to call them to let them know where I was (bc i didn't have time to sit in the line). They took the phone off the hook. Total wait for order 26 minutes.

Trip 2:
I'm a slow learner apparently. I don't know why I acceped another Doordash order for this location, but I thought I'd give them another chance. Again I've been here 18 min and havent made it to the intercom.
UPDATE: 30 min waiting on this order and they inform me that they're out of cookies. Completely out. This order had 2 cookie totes (26 cookies). These cookies are break and bake and literally take minutes to bake but they couldn't be bothered with it at any point during my 30 minute wait. Total wait 33 min.

The bags have stickers on them so you cant check to make sure the order is right. I'd put $100 on the food being wrong in some way.

It honestly seemed like the employees were trying to make it a horrible experience. Maybe they thought we would go away? Probably goes without saying, but definitely no apology/thank you/attempt at being friendly in the least.

How much you think I made off these orders tonight? $6 before gas and taxes...not to mention whatever other orders that came up that I missed out on. Makes me want to Karen.

I am a regular to this McDonalds because i have no choice; it is the only 24/7 restaurant in the vicinity and it is constantly short staffed with extremely lazy and rude people. Please do something about this mcdonalds. There should be no reason why the system is working perfectly fine during the day but somehow malfunctions every night. Every time I come here it makes my mood significantly worse because something ALWAYS goes wrong and it is yalls fault. I wont stop leaving bad reviews until something is done because I cant put up with this service any more.

text:
I really just don't understand why the owners of this site expended the effort and the costs to completely renovate this McDonald's, yet apparently are not in the least bit concerned over how poorly it's overnight sales have got to be reflecting lower sales than before the facelift.  If the owners would just take 10 minutes to read their most recent Google reviews, they could make the desperately needed changes that the night crew currently are so terribly in need of immediately.  I assume, however, their apparent lack of concern all around with how poorly run this site has been doing business must mean that they're not concerned about their profits. And that's really sad because that translates to customers that upper management doesn't care about us and our concerns.

There are 2 things I know to be 100% CONSISTENT and TRUE about this McDonald's:

1. That for any given hours between midnight and 4:00AM you'll be turned away by the staff because their "system is down again".  More than likely, it'll be told to you  over the drive thru speaker in a short/abrubt/rude manner and/or tone.

2.  That, should you win the lottery during those late night night hours and actually make it past the drive thru speaker's gatekeeper, and give them your order...when you arrive at the window to pay & receive your anticipated meal, there is a 75% chance the staff will say anything to you, beyond the amount you're due to pay them, (because they're so deeply preoccupied in their own interpersonal conversations behind the coumter), and there is a 100% chance that you will NEVER be sent off with a "THANK YOU!!". Nice staff but this place is kind of a mess

name: Hill Allen
text: Today I went through the drive-through at this location.  After the pre-recorded message giving me the "special" and saying place my order when I am ready, I placed my order.  No response came and a couple minutes later a voice came over the speaker asking me if I was ready to place my order.  I again placed my order.  When I was done a voice came over and said they couldn't hear me because I was too far from the microphone.  I then leaned out of my window as far as I could and as loudly as I could placed my order.  I was again told they couldn't hear me. I said I have placed my order three times. The woman came on and said I didn't have to have an attitude with her and that I needed to be louder. I started to place the order again, but got no response.  I yelled, "Can you hear me?"  No response.  "Hello?!"  No response. Then in a normal tone say I will just pull up and order at the window.  To that I get a response of "OK."   When I get to the window the cashier asks what I will have.  I start placing my order with her and a woman with a microphone comes around the corner and interrupts and tells me that it's not her fault she couldn't hear me.  At this point I tell her then must be something wrong with their equipment because a customer should not have to lean out of the window and scream their order and still not be heard.  She gave me a head bob and said there's no reason to be that way and walked away.  I then was able to place my order with the cashier.  I said to her that at some other fast food establishments the person taking the order gives you their name as you order to ensure better customer service.  She then replied in a snippy was. "Nope, we don't give you our names here."  I said "I would guess not, or it would make it to easy for customers to complain about poor service."   When I pulled forward the girl handing me our food was polite and all smiles.  I complimented her and told the manager behind her that it was nice to have a happy person at that window when the people taking the order were terribly rude. I don't know if the equipment was faulty or if the drive through person was just having a laugh at my expense watching me through the camera trying in vain to place my order.    Either way, the aggressive nature of the worker was completely uncalled for and unacceptable.

I recommend that you be careful because the entrance is a little awkward especially during high traffic hours. It sits in a shopping center with other stores like Ollies, Pier 1 Imports, 5 Below, Play it Again Sports, Creative Nail Spa, ULTA Beauty, David's Bridal, and JoAnn's Fabric. I ordered McChicken combos and Cheeseburger combos for my nieces and nephews. The children said their food was delicious. I had a pineapple mango smoothie, it was very refreshing on a hot summer day. The customer service was very pleasant.

Update - The construction is finished so you don't have to worry about that anymore.

text:
Do yourself a favor and avoid this place in the mornings, especially if you have anywhere to be. It consistently has one drive-thru employee and a line so long you can easily wait ten to fifteen minutes for your order.
However I kept giving it a chance, mainly because it’s on the way to work and I need coffee in the morning. Just a coffee. But they can’t even get that right. On several occasions now the girl has handed me a large cup of black coffee (which I don’t drink) and nodded when I asked if there was cream and sugar in it. I didn’t realize her error until much further down the road and I don’t have time in the morning to squabble about a $2.15 loss or the patience to sit another fifteen minutes in the drive-thru.
This morning I called back and spoke to a curt and frazzled “manager” on the phone (She said her name was Shameka) whose response to my complaints only left me more frustrated than I was before.
Don’t waste your time at this location. Drive further down 31 and go to the one across from Ellis piano. They are friendlier, faster, and much more efficient.

text: I work overnight nearby. My choices to eat around 2 or 3 am are now just these guys and taco bell. I've been told plenty of times that lunch stops being served at 3am, but was just told that it's "different every night". It's okay, I'll take my money to taco bell. The fries were stale last time and the burger was so greasy I threw it up afterwards. I can only speak for the overnight shift but I do the same shift for customer service and please every single guest I come into contact with. Overnight staff there needs to be fired and replaced with better mannered and better spoken employees. Like I said, last time I checked, "Brefuss only" started at 3am, not whenever you feel like it.

text:
In the future when someone  orders something call it back to them so you can make sure they get what they want.  I'm on a very strict diet and I was on my way to work when I ordered a "steak egg and cheese mcmuffin"  I chose the Mcmuffin because it has less carbs and is allowed on my diet..  I got to work and was going to eat before I went in. And instead of a mcmuffin I have a steak egg and cheese BAGEL... carbs galore!  ... so now I stuck with it because I don't have time to turn around.  So.. since I know I will not be getting the chance to eat again till about 2 pm (it is 7:30 am by the way), I'm forced to take it apart and just eat the egg and steak with my fingers..... yeah great start to my morning.

I seriously hope that one day someone will shut you guys down... it's pathetic. .. your whole business needs a makeover!

I'm also extremely thankful that they are continuing to adhere to the Covid-19 health guidelines, with everyone wearing masks and gloves, and touchless drive thru.

Thank you for holding steady at this location.

name: notthebeesxoxo
text:
This is the best DD in town. I love DD coffee but struggled for a while to find a DD that can consistently make a drink right. Every place, they either made it too strong, not strong enough, not sweet enough, too sweet... Just tons of issues and lots of wasted money on coffees I couldn't even force myself to finish.

Then they opened this location and they are the most consistent DD I've been to and I go here every single day during the week. The people are also so nice and the drive thru, even when busy, is so fast! There could be 7 cars in line and I'll still be done in 10 mins or less.

text:
I love coming here to get coffee. Today though there was a lady with blue hair, I didn’t get her name down though. She showed excellent customer service to the two girls in front of me but when it came time to take my order specifically she was showing terrible customer service...but passively. Like she didn’t want to take my order but had to since I was already there. She didn’t ask if I wanted my receipt and she didn’t give me a straw and sugar for my coffee either like she did the other two girls in front of me. I had to ask, and when I did she seemed a bit hesitant to give them to me. Like I was taking up her time. I was having kind of a bad day that day and this is why we (especially if you work in customer service) should always strive to at least TRY to treat people with decency...I’m also aware we all have our bad days though and nobodies perfect. You never know what other people are gong though truly. I’m a bit skeptical on coming back here because I don’t wanna have another employee lowkey making me feel bad, especially if I might be having another bad day next time as well. I’ll just have to go to the one by the mall and wait in The line for a little minute, might take longer but they’re customer service is always on point.
Anyway hope Whoever is reading has a great day

name: Tim Cheatwood
text: Fast food gets a bad rap more often than not. Though, it is not always warranted. This McDonalds, on the other hand, deserves the reputation that stigmatizes fast food everywhere. We don't frequent McDonalds anymore because this one is so bad, but the kids beg to go anytime they see the golden arches. Tonight, since we were in a hurry, I swung by the drive-thru for what I thought would be a quick visit. There were only 3 cars in the lane in front of us when we arrived. This McDonalds has 2 lanes, supposedly for greater efficiency, and we thought it would move pretty quickly. It did not. To my surprise, when we approached the menu to order we were promptly greeted. I asked the cashier to hold for a moment while I finalized the kids' orders. When I began our order, I informed the cashier I wanted a Double Quarter Pounder with Cheese Meal, large sized with a Diet Coke. Yes a Diet Coke. You can laugh. I find the humor in it also. The cashier rang up the meal as I ordered and no sooner than I had gotten it out of my mouth they rudely replied, "is that all?" In case you don't know me, that irritates me to my core. If that was all I wanted, I would have said so. The correct question that should be asked politely is, "what else can I get for you today?" We have a decent sized family (4 kids), and my wife is picky, so it can take some time to get everyone's orders placed. I know they have metrics to meet, similar to an average handle time for a call center, but like in the call center business, you give the appropriate amount of time to the customer, while being as efficient as possible, then focus on making the next interaction shorter to compensate. Before I could continue with the rest of the order, I had to correct the cashier because they rang up a medium sized meal. Once "corrected" I asked if they got the drink large as well. The cashier replied they did. I informed them the screen says otherwise and in order to correct it, they canceled the order and rang it up again. I continued to place the rest of our order, having to repeat myself multiple times because they could not seem to ring it up correctly and when they did not put "add lettuce" on the screen for the McChicken, I had to ask multiple times if they got it. The cashier rudely replied, "it already comes with lettuce." Had they said that in the first place we could have saved some time. We finally got our order placed, repeated, and the total provided and we headed to the window. All the cars in the drive-thru merged together into the service line in what appeared to be the correct order for which we took our turns at the menu, but when we arrived at the payment window they tried to charge us for the wrong order. We paid for our order, then it was off to the service window for pick-up. The first thing they tried to hand me was, you guessed it, a Medium Diet Coke. I informed the attendant it was supposed to be large and they looked at me like I was trying to get something I didn't order (at least that was my perception). They pulled the drink back through the window, looked at the screen of their POS (Point of Sale) system, then exclaimed, "Oh... I see what they did." They can have their look back as well since I definitely paid for a large, but I kept that remark to myself. They gave me the other drinks, then the food, and left me waiting for my Large Diet Coke. While waiting, and after they gave me the drink, I proceeded to check the labels, not the individual sandwiches. After all of the waiting and grief we had to deal with on their side, I just wanted to make sure the labels were at least correct. Then, the original cashier that took my order came and hung halfway out the window to ask me, "Sir, can you please pull up so we can assist these other customers?" To which, I promptly replied, "Sure, just as soon as I make sure I received all of my food." I wasn't about to go through all of that again. We had received all of the food, and I drove away with the cashier still staring at me like a buffoon. How rude. That's all I can say.

name: Katie Reynolds
text:
(Context: Went inside to place a to-go order. It was not busy at all. Ordered 2 sandwiches and a fountain drink. Asked to fill personal water bottle with water. Request was denied because water dispenser was behind counter. So, asked for a cup of water instead. Got receipt and realized they charged $0.75 for the water.)
What restaurant charges $0.75 for a cup of water? I cannot rationalize this decision.
Was it to prevent customers from buying water and nothing else? Doubtful. Water was not the only thing I ordered; Was it to offset the cost of the water and cup? Highly unlikely. Maybe $0.10 or $0.20 would more than cover it. Was it to prevent customers from using their water cups to steal fountain drinks? Maybe. If so, the restaurant should find a fix that doesn't lead to honest customers unknowingly paying a ridiculous price for something which is usually free at most places.
Additionally, the quality of the food was sub-par. The McChicken was overloaded with mayo, the burger was mediocre, and the cup of Coke tasted abnormal compared to experiences at other McDonald's.
Giving 2 stars because I at least didn't get sick.

text: Pulled up to the speaker, heard someone mumble, so I placed my order.  Waited, waited and waited.  No one spoke. I pulled up behind a truck waiting at the window.  Waited 8and waited and waited some more.  At this point it had been 15 minutes.  The truck in front of me had honked his horn about 3 times. I finally call the store, tell them they have someone at the window.  Finally place my order at the window, appoligized for having to call paid for my order and waited. And waited. And waited. The entire time Im waiting the girl who took my order is dancing, like booty dancing. Finally get my food, fries are stone cold, they forgot my sauce and never got an apology or a thank you have a good day, nothing. Also didn't get a receipt!

name: Chris Adams
text:
Best McDonald's to go to if you routinely want your order to made incorrectly or thrown together as if it were done by a three year old toddler.  You can also expect your drink to be handed to you with some of it running down the sides of the cup and this is before you have received your food so you have no napkins to wipe it off with.

For me, visiting this place is more entertainment than for food needs.  It's comical how poorly operated it is yet also sad to see so much potential going to waste.  I wouldn't go here at all if it were not for the rest of my family liking their food.  In fact, half the time I stop there I get them food and then I go to Chic-fil-a to order mine.  At least there I can get exactly what I order that is not just thrown together and my drink is no running all over the cup.

One more thing about this place.  Forget ever getting any type of milkshake.  I've lived in this area since before this place was even built and since it opened their ice cream or milkshake machine has always been out of order.

UPDATE: 1/11/2018
As usual these people can't get an order right to save their own lives.  I ordered two chicken biscuit combos and guess what was in the bag...just one.  Instead of listening they seemed to have gotten totally distracted by what type of chicken biscuit meal.

I wish my family didn't like this place so I wouldn't have to deal with the nonsense here.  OR  perhaps the owner could take some action to ensure that it is run properly...somehow your competitor right there by you, Chic-fil-a, get's it done right.

UPDATE: 10/2019
Nothing has improved.

Order still can't be taken or prepared properly.  If you're going in then there won't be any salt, pepper, or napkins available.  No creamer for coffee.  You literally have to ask for everything.  You have to ask a group of people who clearly don't want to be there for everything you need ie; ketchup packs or whatever and believe me they aren't interested in hearing your request.

The tables and seats are dirty and despite the kiosk, which those are good, you still have to go stand in line to get your cups because they won't bring the drinks with the food.  So, they put in a kiosk to reduce lines then force you back into the line...you can't make this kind of stuff up.

name: Ben
text: I never realized it was possible to be too incompetent to run a McDonald’s even somewhat efficiently until trying to get food at this location. The one time they somehow managed to get me through the drive-thru within the span of an hour they still somehow got the order wrong when I was one of two cars there. Tonight I thought I’d give them another chance and grab some food on the way into work. I thought wrong. I pull up to the drove through and there’s maybe 4 cars there including me so it was by no means a rush, especially for normal dinner hours, so I thought “nice, I should be able to get my food and make it to work in plenty of time!” I thought wrong. So it takes about 10 minutes for the 2 cars in front of me to get their orders in and it thought “ This is fine, they probably just have some big/complicated orders.” I thought wrong. I get to the window and the operator says “one moment please.” So it thought “that’s fine, he’s probably gotta take care of a simple task real quick.” I thought wrong. After more than 5 minutes of waiting at the speaker I had to just leave the line as I would’ve been late to work had I waited the whole time it would’ve taken to get my food. Some say the people who were ahead of me in line are still waiting to get their order or for it to be correct to this day. So in short, save yourself the trouble and go to a different restaurant, especially if you’re on any kind of a schedule that doesn’t permit an hour of waiting, unless you want to leave a McDonald’s angry, hungry, or probably both.
